{"type":"message","id":"f44dfe27","parentId":"81b9d13a","timestamp":"2026-04-16T10:57:06.934Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_lhb2k7l8dc8x_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\ntitle: \"Active Memory\"\nsummary: \"A plugin-owned blocking memory sub-agent that injects relevant memory into interactive chat sessions\"\nread_when:\n  - You want to understand what active memory is for\n  - You want to turn active memory on for a conversational agent\n  - You want to tune active memory behavior without enabling it everywhere\n---\n\n# Active Memory\n\nActive memory is an optional plugin-owned blocking memory sub-agent that runs\nbefore the main reply for eligible conversational sessions.\n\nIt exists because most memory systems are capable but reactive. They rely on\nthe main agent to decide when to search memory, or on the user to say things\nlike \"remember this\" or \"search memory.\" By then, the moment where memory would\nhave made the reply feel natural has already passed.\n\nActive memory gives the system one bounded chance to surface relevant memory\nbefore the main reply is generated.\n\n## Paste This Into Your Agent\n\nPaste this into your agent if you want it to enable Active Memory with a\nself-contained, safe-default setup:\n\n```json5\n{\n  plugins: {\n    entries: {\n      \"active-memory\": {\n        enabled: true,\n        config: {\n          enabled: true,\n          agents: [\"main\"],\n          allowedChatTypes: [\"direct\"],\n          modelFallback: \"google/gemini-3-flash\",\n          queryMode: \"recent\",\n          promptStyle: \"balanced\",\n          timeoutMs: 15000,\n          maxSummaryChars: 220,\n          persistTranscripts: false,\n          logging: true,\n        },\n      },\n    },\n  },\n}\n```\n\nThis turns the plugin on for the `main` agent, keeps it limited to direct-message\nstyle sessions by default, lets it inherit the current session model first, and\nuses the configured fallback model only if no explicit or inherited model is\navailable.\n\nAfter that, restart the gateway:\n\n```bash\nopenclaw gateway\n```\n\nTo inspect it live in a conversation:\n\n```text\n/verbose on\n/trace on\n```\n\n## Turn active memory on\n\nThe safest setup is:\n\n1. enable the plugin\n2. target one conversational agent\n3. keep logging on only while tuning\n\nStart with this in `openclaw.json`:\n\n```json5\n\n[721 more lines in file. Use offset=81 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776337026872}}
{"type":"message","id":"f3e60116","parentId":"f44dfe27","timestamp":"2026-04-16T10:57:06.989Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_lhb2k7l8dc8x_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nsummary: \"Context engine: pluggable context assembly, compaction, and subagent lifecycle\"\nread_when:\n  - You want to understand how OpenClaw assembles model context\n  - You are switching between the legacy engine and a plugin engine\n  - You are building a context engine plugin\ntitle: \"Context Engine\"\n---\n\n# Context Engine\n\nA **context engine** controls how OpenClaw builds model context for each run.\nIt decides which messages to include, how to summarize older history, and how\nto manage context across subagent boundaries.\n\nOpenClaw ships with a built-in `legacy` engine. Plugins can register\nalternative engines that replace the active context-engine lifecycle.\n\n## Quick start\n\nCheck which engine is active:\n\n```bash\nopenclaw doctor\n# or inspect config directly:\ncat ~/.openclaw/openclaw.json | jq '.plugins.slots.contextEngine'\n```\n\n### Installing a context engine plugin\n\nContext engine plugins are installed like any other OpenClaw plugin. Install\nfirst, then select the engine in the slot:\n\n```bash\n# Install from npm\nopenclaw plugins install @martian-engineering/lossless-claw\n\n# Or install from a local path (for development)\nopenclaw plugins install -l ./my-context-engine\n```\n\nThen enable the plugin and select it as the active engine in your config:\n\n```json5\n// openclaw.json\n{\n  plugins: {\n    slots: {\n      contextEngine: \"lossless-claw\", // must match the plugin's registered engine id\n    },\n    entries: {\n      \"lossless-claw\": {\n        enabled: true,\n        // Plugin-specific config goes here (see the plugin's docs)\n      },\n    },\n  },\n}\n```\n\nRestart the gateway after installing and configuring.\n\nTo switch back to the built-in engine, set `contextEngine` to `\"legacy\"` (or\nremove the key entirely — `\"legacy\"` is the default).\n\n## How it works\n\nEvery time OpenClaw runs a model prompt, the context engine participates at\nfour lifecycle points:\n\n1. **Ingest** — called when a new message is added to the session. The engine\n   can store or index the message in its own data store.\n2. **Assemble** — called before each model run. The engine returns an ordered\n   set of messages (and an optional `systemPromptAddition`) that fit within\n   the token budget.\n3. **Compact** — called when the context window is full, or when the user runs\n   `/compact`. The engine summarizes older history to free space.\n4. **After turn** — called after a run completes. The engine can persist state,\n   trigger background compaction, or update indexes.\n\n\n[206 more lines in file. Use offset=81 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776337026935}}
{"type":"message","id":"9a24d290","parentId":"f3e60116","timestamp":"2026-04-16T10:57:07.046Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_lhb2k7l8dc8x_3","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nsummary: \"Delegate architecture: running OpenClaw as a named agent on behalf of an organization\"\ntitle: Delegate Architecture\nread_when: \"You want an agent with its own identity that acts on behalf of humans in an organization.\"\nstatus: active\n---\n\n# Delegate Architecture\n\nGoal: run OpenClaw as a **named delegate** — an agent with its own identity that acts \"on behalf of\" people in an organization. The agent never impersonates a human. It sends, reads, and schedules under its own account with explicit delegation permissions.\n\nThis extends [Multi-Agent Routing](/concepts/multi-agent) from personal use into organizational deployments.\n\n## What is a delegate?\n\nA **delegate** is an OpenClaw agent that:\n\n- Has its **own identity** (email address, display name, calendar).\n- Acts **on behalf of** one or more humans — never pretends to be them.\n- Operates under **explicit permissions** granted by the organization's identity provider.\n- Follows **[standing orders](/automation/standing-orders)** — rules defined in the agent's `AGENTS.md` that specify what it may do autonomously vs. what requires human approval (see [Cron Jobs](/automation/cron-jobs) for scheduled execution).\n\nThe delegate model maps directly to how executive assistants work: they have their own credentials, send mail \"on behalf of\" their principal, and follow a defined scope of authority.\n\n## Why delegates?\n\nOpenClaw's default mode is a **personal assistant** — one human, one agent. Delegates extend this to organizations:\n\n| Personal mode               | Delegate mode                                  |\n| --------------------------- | ---------------------------------------------- |\n| Agent uses your credentials | Agent has its own credentials                  |\n| Replies come from you       | Replies come from the delegate, on your behalf |\n| One principal               | One or many principals                         |\n| Trust boundary = you        | Trust boundary = organization policy           |\n\nDelegates solve two problems:\n\n1. **Accountability**: messages sent by the agent are clearly from the agent, not a human.\n2. **Scope control**: the identity provider enforces what the delegate can access, independent of OpenClaw's own tool policy.\n\n## Capability tiers\n\nStart with the lowest tier that meets your needs. Escalate only when the use case demands it.\n\n### Tier 1: Read-Only + Draft\n\nThe delegate can **read** organizational data and **draft** messages for human review. Nothing is sent without approval.\n\n- Email: read inbox, summarize threads, flag items for human action.\n- Calendar: read events, surface conflicts, summarize the day.\n- Files: read shared documents, summarize content.\n\nThis tier requires only read permissions from the identity provider. The agent does not write to any mailbox or calendar — drafts and proposals are delivered via chat for the human to act on.\n\n### Tier 2: Send on Behalf\n\nThe delegate can **send** messages and **create** calendar events under its own identity. Recipients see \"Delegate Name on behalf of Principal Name.\"\n\n- Email: send with \"on behalf of\" header.\n- Calendar: create events, send invitations.\n- Chat: post to channels as the delegate identity.\n\nThis tier requires send-on-behalf (or delegate) permissions.\n\n### Tier 3: Proactive\n\nThe delegate operates **autonomously** on a schedule, executing standing orders without per-action human approval. Humans review output asynchronously.\n\n- Morning briefings delivered to a channel.\n- Automated social media publishing via approved content queues.\n- Inbox triage with auto-categorization and flagging.\n\nThis tier combines Tier 2 permissions with [Cron Jobs](/automation/cron-jobs) and [Standing Orders](/automation/standing-orders).\n\n> **Security warning**: Tier 3 requires careful configuration of hard blocks — actions the agent must never take regardless of instruction. Complete the prerequisites below before granting any identity provider permissions.\n\n## Prerequisites: isolation and hardening\n\n> **Do this first.** Before you grant any credentials or identity provider access, lock down the delegate's boundaries. The steps in this section define what the agent **cannot** do — establish these constraints before giving it the ability to do anything.\n\n\n[228 more lines in file. Use offset=81 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776337026990}}
{"type":"message","id":"d662fb00","parentId":"9a24d290","timestamp":"2026-04-16T10:57:13.014Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me also read some other new files like retry.md, soul.md, and the expanded features.md:","thinkingSignature":"ca9ec550aedfb9603cb4a0b81c41bede6d31334387b84097805d0b4f0a41eff4"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_brawn1xkkoe5_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/ai/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/retry.md","limit":60}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_brawn1xkkoe5_2","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/ai/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/soul.md","limit":60}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_brawn1xkkoe5_3","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/ai/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/usage-tracking.md","limit":60}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":71373,"output":195,"cacheRead":21036,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":92604,"cost":{"input":0.021411899999999998,"output":0.000234,"cacheRead":0.0012621599999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.022908059999999997}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776337027048,"responseId":"062ff382dbd4545d4b6173f44bcb9b90"}}
{"type":"message","id":"cc37d6f4","parentId":"d662fb00","timestamp":"2026-04-16T10:57:14.059Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_brawn1xkkoe5_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nsummary: \"Retry policy for outbound provider calls\"\nread_when:\n  - Updating provider retry behavior or defaults\n  - Debugging provider send errors or rate limits\ntitle: \"Retry Policy\"\n---\n\n# Retry policy\n\n## Goals\n\n- Retry per HTTP request, not per multi-step flow.\n- Preserve ordering by retrying only the current step.\n- Avoid duplicating non-idempotent operations.\n\n## Defaults\n\n- Attempts: 3\n- Max delay cap: 30000 ms\n- Jitter: 0.1 (10 percent)\n- Provider defaults:\n  - Telegram min delay: 400 ms\n  - Discord min delay: 500 ms\n\n## Behavior\n\n### Discord\n\n- Retries only on rate-limit errors (HTTP 429).\n- Uses Discord `retry_after` when available, otherwise exponential backoff.\n\n### Telegram\n\n- Retries on transient errors (429, timeout, connect/reset/closed, temporarily unavailable).\n- Uses `retry_after` when available, otherwise exponential backoff.\n- Markdown parse errors are not retried; they fall back to plain text.\n\n## Configuration\n\nSet retry policy per provider in `~/.openclaw/openclaw.json`:\n\n```json5\n{\n  channels: {\n    telegram: {\n      retry: {\n        attempts: 3,\n        minDelayMs: 400,\n        maxDelayMs: 30000,\n        jitter: 0.1,\n      },\n    },\n    discord: {\n      retry: {\n        attempts: 3,\n        minDelayMs: 500,\n        maxDelayMs: 30000,\n        jitter: 0.1,\n      },\n\n[10 more lines in file. Use offset=61 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776337034002}}
{"type":"message","id":"f7db583a","parentId":"cc37d6f4","timestamp":"2026-04-16T10:57:14.113Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_brawn1xkkoe5_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nsummary: \"Use SOUL.md to give your OpenClaw agent an actual voice instead of generic assistant sludge\"\nread_when:\n  - You want your agent to sound less generic\n  - You are editing SOUL.md\n  - You want a stronger personality without breaking safety or brevity\ntitle: \"SOUL.md Personality Guide\"\n---\n\n# SOUL.md Personality Guide\n\n`SOUL.md` is where your agent's voice lives.\n\nOpenClaw injects it on normal sessions, so it has real weight. If your agent\nsounds bland, hedgy, or weirdly corporate, this is usually the file to fix.\n\n## What belongs in SOUL.md\n\nPut the stuff that changes how the agent feels to talk to:\n\n- tone\n- opinions\n- brevity\n- humor\n- boundaries\n- default level of bluntness\n\nDo **not** turn it into:\n\n- a life story\n- a changelog\n- a security policy dump\n- a giant wall of vibes with no behavioral effect\n\nShort beats long. Sharp beats vague.\n\n## Why this works\n\nThis lines up with OpenAI's prompt guidance:\n\n- The prompt engineering guide says high-level behavior, tone, goals, and\n  examples belong in the high-priority instruction layer, not buried in the\n  user turn.\n- The same guide recommends treating prompts like something you iterate on,\n  pin, and evaluate, not magical prose you write once and forget.\n\nFor OpenClaw, `SOUL.md` is that layer.\n\nIf you want better personality, write stronger instructions. If you want stable\npersonality, keep them concise and versioned.\n\nOpenAI refs:\n\n- [Prompt engineering](https://developers.openai.com/api/docs/guides/prompt-engineering)\n- [Message roles and instruction following](https://developers.openai.com/api/docs/guides/prompt-engineering#message-roles-and-instruction-following)\n\n## The Molty prompt\n\nPaste this into your agent and let it rewrite `SOUL.md`.\n\n\n[51 more lines in file. Use offset=61 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776337034059}}
{"type":"message","id":"ee16d9d9","parentId":"f7db583a","timestamp":"2026-04-16T10:57:14.167Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_brawn1xkkoe5_3","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nsummary: \"Usage tracking surfaces and credential requirements\"\nread_when:\n  - You are wiring provider usage/quota surfaces\n  - You need to explain usage tracking behavior or auth requirements\ntitle: \"Usage Tracking\"\n---\n\n# Usage tracking\n\n## What it is\n\n- Pulls provider usage/quota directly from their usage endpoints.\n- No estimated costs; only the provider-reported windows.\n- Human-readable status output is normalized to `X% left`, even when an\n  upstream API reports consumed quota, remaining quota, or only raw counts.\n- Session-level `/status` and `session_status` can fall back to the latest\n  transcript usage entry when the live session snapshot is sparse. That\n  fallback fills missing token/cache counters, can recover the active runtime\n  model label, and prefers the larger prompt-oriented total when session\n  metadata is missing or smaller. Existing nonzero live values still win.\n\n## Where it shows up\n\n- `/status` in chats: emoji‑rich status card with session tokens + estimated cost (API key only). Provider usage shows for the **current model provider** when available as a normalized `X% left` window.\n- `/usage off|tokens|full` in chats: per-response usage footer (OAuth shows tokens only).\n- `/usage cost` in chats: local cost summary aggregated from OpenClaw session logs.\n- CLI: `openclaw status --usage` prints a full per-provider breakdown.\n- CLI: `openclaw channels list` prints the same usage snapshot alongside provider config (use `--no-usage` to skip).\n- macOS menu bar: “Usage” section under Context (only if available).\n\n## Providers + credentials\n\n- **Anthropic (Claude)**: OAuth tokens in auth profiles.\n- **GitHub Copilot**: OAuth tokens in auth profiles.\n- **Gemini CLI**: OAuth tokens in auth profiles.\n  - JSON usage falls back to `stats`; `stats.cached` is normalized into\n    `cacheRead`.\n- **OpenAI Codex**: OAuth tokens in auth profiles (accountId used when present).\n- **MiniMax**: API key or MiniMax OAuth auth profile. OpenClaw treats\n  `minimax`, `minimax-cn`, and `minimax-portal` as the same MiniMax quota\n  surface, prefers stored MiniMax OAuth when present, and otherwise falls back\n  to `MINIMAX_CODE_PLAN_KEY`, `MINIMAX_CODING_API_KEY`, or `MINIMAX_API_KEY`.\n  MiniMax's raw `usage_percent` / `usagePercent` fields mean **remaining**\n  quota, so OpenClaw inverts them before display; count-based fields win when\n  present.\n  - Coding-plan window labels come from provider hours/minutes fields when\n    present, then fall back to the `start_time` / `end_time` span.\n  - If the coding-plan endpoint returns `model_remains`, OpenClaw prefers the\n    chat-model entry, derives the window label from timestamps when explicit\n    `window_hours` / `window_minutes` fields are absent, and includes the model\n    name in the plan label.\n- **Xiaomi MiMo**: API key via env/config/auth store (`XIAOMI_API_KEY`).\n- **z.ai**: API key via env/config/auth store.\n\nUsage is hidden when no usable provider usage auth can be resolved. Providers\ncan supply plugin-specific usage auth logic; otherwise OpenClaw falls back to\nmatching OAuth/API-key credentials from auth profiles, environment variables,\nor config.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776337034113}}
{"type":"message","id":"c8974893","parentId":"ee16d9d9","timestamp":"2026-04-16T10:57:25.029Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have enough information. Let me also check the new files in tools/ and other areas that were new:\n- `openai-whisper.md` was already known\n- Let me check if there's a `presence.md` I should read\n\nActually, I have enough to understand what's new in 2026.4.14 vs 2026.4.9. Key new features:\n\n1. **Active Memory** - blocking memory sub-agent that runs before main reply\n2. **Context Engine** - pluggable context assembly (replaces legacy engine)\n3. **Delegate Architecture** - organizational deployment with delegate identity\n4. **SOUL.md Personality Guide** - official guidance on writing SOUL.md\n\n\n5. **Usage Tracking** - per-provider quota tracking with X% left\n6. **Retry Policy** - per-provider retry configuration\n\nNow I need to update the framework document to reflect these additions. I should add new sections for Active Memory, Context Engine, and the other features I've identified, then update the table of contents accordingly.","thinkingSignature":"58433f3ec7eeb939a6125c5ef882feda6cf40c5a94934c7cdb2fe2ef14b04ab2"},{"type":"text","text":"好，已读完新增文档。现在更新文件，加上这些 **2026.4.14 新增/重大更新**：\n\n- **Active Memory** — 阻塞式记忆子 agent，回复前主动注入相关记忆\n- **Context Engine** — 可插拔的上下文引擎（支持插件替换 legacy）\n- **Delegate Architecture** — 组织级部署，agent 以自己身份代表组织行动\n- **Usage Tracking** — 各 provider 用量追踪（X% left）\n- **Retry Policy** — 渠道级别重试策略配置\n- **SOUL.md Personality Guide** — 官方人格撰写指南\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_nuvn1vq5men0_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/main/OpenClaw-v2026.4.9-完整功能框架.md","limit":50}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":73086,"output":399,"cacheRead":21036,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":94521,"cost":{"input":0.0219258,"output":0.0004788,"cacheRead":0.0012621599999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.02366676}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776337034169,"responseId":"062ff3892b1752542c40c6d815f40d38"}}
{"type":"message","id":"b1d03b29","parentId":"c8974893","timestamp":"2026-04-16T10:57:25.943Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_nuvn1vq5men0_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# OpenClaw v2026.4.9 完整功能框架\n\n> 生成时间：2026-04-16 | 版本：2026.4.9（npm 最新：2026.4.14）\n\n---\n\n## 目录\n\n1. [核心定位](#1-核心定位)\n2. [架构总览](#2-架构总览)\n3. [Gateway 核心](#3-gateway-核心)\n4. [Agent 循环](#4-agent-循环)\n5. [Bootstrap 系统](#5-bootstrap-系统)\n6. [Prompt 组装](#6-prompt-组装)\n7. [三层记忆系统](#7-三层记忆系统)\n8. [v8 路由系统](#8-v8-路由系统)\n9. [工具系统](#9-工具系统)\n10. [Skills 系统](#10-skills-系统)\n11. [自动化：Cron + Hooks](#11-自动化cron--hooks)\n12. [会话管理](#12-会话管理)\n13. [消息队列](#13-消息队列)\n14. [媒体支持](#14-媒体支持)\n15. [渠道系统](#15-渠道系统)\n16. [节点系统](#16-节点系统)\n17. [Web UI 与远程访问](#17-web-ui-与远程访问)\n18. [安全机制](#18-安全机制)\n19. [模型系统](#19-模型系统)\n20. [流式输出与 Chunking](#20-流式输出与-chunking)\n21. [沙箱隔离](#21-沙箱隔离)\n22. [多 Agent 路由](#22-多-agent-路由)\n23. [插件系统](#23-插件系统)\n24. [ACP 协议](#24-acp-协议)\n25. [Lobster 工作流](#25-lobster-工作流)\n26. [Task Flow 任务流](#26-task-flow-任务流)\n27. [Compaction 压缩机制](#27-compaction-压缩机制)\n28. [配置系统](#28-配置系统)\n29. [CLI 命令全览](#29-cli-命令全览)\n30. [当前运行状态](#30-当前运行状态)\n\n---\n\n## 1. 核心定位\n\n**OpenClaw = 本地 AI Gateway + 多渠道消息中枢 + 推理引擎编排器**\n\n| 维度 | 说明 |\n|------|------|\n| **本质** | 部署在自己硬件上的自托管服务，数据完全自主 |\n| **核心价值** | 一个进程同时对接所有聊天渠道，统一连接到 AI 推理引擎 |\n| **差异化** | Agent 原生（工具/记忆/多Agent路由）、自托管、多渠道 |\n\n[1578 more lines in file. Use offset=51 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776337045892}}
{"type":"message","id":"734f349d","parentId":"b1d03b29","timestamp":"2026-04-16T10:58:22.433Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I need to update the file to add the new features. I'll update:\n1. Title and version header\n2. Add new sections to TOC\n3. Add new sections after appropriate existing sections\n\nLet me do this with edits. The key changes:\n1. Header: 2026.4.9 → 2026.4.14\n2. TOC: Add items 31-36 for new features\n3. Add new sections after section 30\n\nLet me do targeted edits:\n1. Update version header\n2. Add new TOC entries\n3. Add new sections at the end\n\nI'll do it in a few edits.","thinkingSignature":"366032bcd13c9d7cacafe11865d8f7f802ab9e7bca353301bfb52027dbea0d58"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_t192af6ug0ys_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/main/OpenClaw-v2026.4.9-完整功能框架.md","edits":[{"oldText":"# OpenClaw v2026.4.9 完整功能框架\n\n> 生成时间：2026-04-16 | 版本：2026.4.9（npm 最新：2026.4.14）","newText":"# OpenClaw v2026.4.14 完整功能框架\n\n> 生成时间：2026-04-16 | 版本：2026.4.14（最新）"},{"oldText":"30. [当前运行状态](#30-当前运行状态)\n\n---\n\n## 1. 核心定位","newText":"30. [当前运行状态](#30-当前运行状态)\n31. [Active Memory 主动记忆](#31-active-memory-主动记忆)\n32. [Context Engine 上下文引擎](#32-context-engine-上下文引擎)\n33. [Delegate Architecture 委托架构](#33-delegate-architecture-委托架构)\n34. [Usage Tracking 用量追踪](#34-usage-tracking-用量追踪)\n35. [Retry Policy 重试策略](#35-retry-policy-重试策略)\n36. [SOUL.md 人格撰写指南](#36-soulmd-人格撰写指南)\n\n---\n\n## 1. 核心定位"},{"oldText":"| 19. 模型系统 |\n\n### 19.1 提供商支持（35+）","newText":"| 19. 模型系统 | 35+ 提供商，含 MiniMax/CodingPlan/Gemini CLI OAuth |"},{"oldText":"---\n\n## 附录：关键文件路径","newText":"---\n\n## 31. Active Memory 主动记忆\n\n### 31.1 定位\n\n**Active Memory** 是一个**插件所有的阻塞式记忆子 agent**，在主回复生成之前运行，为当前对话主动检索并注入相关记忆。\n\n解决大多数记忆系统的核心问题：**被动等待**。传统记忆需要用户说\"记得这个\"或AI自己决定何时搜索，而主动记忆在用户还没开口之前就已经把相关信息带进上下文。\n\n### 31.2 工作流程\n\n```\n用户消息\n    ↓\nActive Memory Sub-Agent（先于主Agent运行）\n    ↓ 检索相关记忆\n记忆片段注入上下文（≤ maxSummaryChars）\n    ↓\n主 Agent 回复生成（已有记忆上下文）\n```\n\n### 31.3 配置\n\n```json5\n{\n  plugins: {\n    entries: {\n      \"active-memory\": {\n        enabled: true,\n        config: {\n          enabled: true,\n          agents: [\"main\"],          // 作用于哪些 agent\n          allowedChatTypes: [\"direct\"], // 仅 DM 会话\n          modelFallback: \"google/gemini-3-flash\",  // 回退模型\n          queryMode: \"recent\",        // 检索模式\n          promptStyle: \"balanced\",\n          timeoutMs: 15000,            // 超时\n          maxSummaryChars: 220,        // 最大注入字符\n          persistTranscripts: false,\n          logging: true,\n        },\n      },\n    },\n  },\n}\n```\n\n### 31.4 关键参数\n\n| 参数 | 说明 |\n|------|------|\n| `agents` | 作用的 agent 列表（如 `[\"main\"]`）|\n| `allowedChatTypes` | 允许的会话类型（`direct` / `group`）|\n| `modelFallback` | 无显式/继承模型时的回退 |\n| `queryMode` | 检索模式（`recent` 等）|\n| `maxSummaryChars` | 注入记忆的最大字符数 |\n| `timeoutMs` | sub-agent 超时（默认 15000ms）|\n\n### 31.5 调试\n\n开启 verbose 和 trace 观察运行：\n```\n/verbose on\n/trace on\n```\n\n---\n\n## 32. Context Engine 上下文引擎\n\n### 32.1 定位\n\n**Context Engine** 是 OpenClaw v2026.4.x 引入的可插拔上下文组件，控制每次模型运行时如何构建 context：包含哪些 messages、如何摘要历史、如何管理 subagent 边界的上下文。\n\n内置 legacy 引擎，可通过插件替换为更高级的上下文管理方案。\n\n### 32.2 生命周期节点\n\n每次模型 prompt，Context Engine 在四个节点参与：\n\n| 节点 | 时机 | 说明 |\n|------|------|------|\n| **Ingest** | 新消息加入 session 时 | 引擎可存储/索引消息 |\n| **Assemble** | 每次模型运行前 | 返回适配 token budget 的有序 messages 列表 |\n| **Compact** | context 满或 `/compact` 时 | 摘要旧历史释放空间 |\n| **After turn** | 运行完成后 | 持久化状态/触发后台压缩/更新索引 |\n\n### 32.3 安装和切换\n\n```bash\n# 从 npm 安装\nopenclaw plugins install @martian-engineering/lossless-claw\n\n# 或从本地路径（开发用）\nopenclaw plugins install -l ./my-context-engine\n```\n\n配置：\n```json5\n{\n  plugins: {\n    slots: {\n      contextEngine: \"lossless-claw\",  // 替换 legacy\n    },\n    entries: {\n      \"lossless-claw\": {\n        enabled: true,\n      },\n    },\n  },\n}\n```\n\n切回内置引擎：`contextEngine: \"legacy\"`（或删除 key）\n\n### 32.4 架构优势\n\n- **无损上下文**：插件引擎可实现更高级的上下文压缩/保留策略\n- **Subagent 上下文继承**：更好的跨 subagent 上下文传递\n- **可测试**：插件形式便于独立验证和对比\n\n---\n\n## 33. Delegate Architecture 委托架构\n\n### 33.1 定位\n\n将 OpenClaw 作为**命名委托（Delegate）**运行——拥有自己身份、代表组织中的人类行事的 Agent。不是冒充人类，而是在自己的账号下操作，有明确的委托权限。\n\n这是 Multi-Agent 路由从**个人助理**扩展到**组织部署**的关键架构。\n\n### 33.2 Delegate vs Personal Assistant\n\n| 维度 | Personal 模式 | Delegate 模式 |\n|------|--------------|--------------|\n| 凭证 | Agent 使用你的凭证 | Agent 有自己的凭证 |\n| 身份 | 回复来自你 | 回复来自 Agent（on your behalf）|\n| 主体 | 一个人 | 一个或多个主体 |\n| 信任边界 | 你 | 组织策略 |\n\n### 33.3 三层能力等级\n\n**Tier 1：只读 + 草稿**\n- 读取组织数据（邮件/日历/文件）\n- 生成摘要供人类参考\n- 不发送任何内容\n\n**Tier 2：代发（Send on Behalf）**\n- 以自己身份发送消息、创建日历事件\n- 收件人看到 \"Delegate Name on behalf of Principal Name\"\n- 需要 send-on-behalf 权限\n\n**Tier 3：主动执行**\n- 按计划自主执行 standing orders\n- 无需逐操作人工审批\n- 需要 Cron Jobs + Standing Orders\n\n### 33.4 Standing Orders\n\nAgent 的 `AGENTS.md` 中定义**常驻规则**：\n- 哪些行为可自主执行\n- 哪些需要人类批准\n- 硬性禁止（hard blocks）—— 无论任何指令都不能执行的操作\n\n### 33.5 安全原则\n\n**Tier 3 必须先完成隔离和加固**：\n1. 锁定 delegate 的所有边界\n2. 配置 hard blocks\n3. 然后才能授予任何凭证或身份提供商权限\n\n---\n\n## 34. Usage Tracking 用量追踪\n\n### 34.1 核心能力\n\n- 从各 provider 的用量端点直接拉取用量/配额数据\n- 仅显示 provider 报告的真实窗口（无估算成本）\n- 归一化为 `X% left` 格式输出\n\n### 34.2 显示位置\n\n| 位置 | 内容 |\n|------|------|\n| `/status` | emoji 状态卡片：session tokens + estimated cost（仅 API key）|\n| `/usage off|tokens|full` | 每轮回复的用量 footer |\n| `/usage cost` | 本地成本汇总（从 session logs 聚合）|\n| CLI: `openclaw status --usage` | 全 provider 用量明细 |\n| CLI: `openclaw channels list` | provider 配置 + 用量快照 |\n\n### 34.3 支持的 Provider\n\n| Provider | 认证方式 |\n|----------|---------|\n| Anthropic (Claude) | OAuth（auth profiles）|\n| GitHub Copilot | OAuth（auth profiles）|\n| Gemini CLI | OAuth（auth profiles）|\n| OpenAI Codex | OAuth（auth profiles）|\n| MiniMax | API key 或 MiniMax OAuth（含 coding-plan 窗口）|\n| Xiaomi MiMo | API key |\n| z.ai | API key |\n\n### 34.4 MiniMax 特殊处理\n\n- `minimax` / `minimax-cn` / `minimax-portal` 视为同一配额面\n- 优先使用存储的 MiniMax OAuth\n- 原始 `usage_percent` / `usagePercent` 为**剩余**配额，OpenClaw 取反后显示\n- coding-plan 窗口标签优先从 hours/minutes 字段读取\n\n---\n\n## 35. Retry Policy 重试策略\n\n### 35.1 目标\n\n- 按 HTTP 请求重试（非多步骤 flow）\n- 通过重试当前 step 保持顺序\n- 避免重复执行非幂等操作\n\n### 35.2 默认值\n\n| 参数 | 默认值 |\n|------|-------|\n| 尝试次数 | 3 |\n| 最大延迟上限 | 30000ms |\n| Jitter | 0.1（10%）|\n| Telegram 最小延迟 | 400ms |\n| Discord 最小延迟 | 500ms |\n\n### 35.3 各渠道行为\n\n**Discord：**\n- 仅在 rate-limit 错误（HTTP 429）时重试\n- 优先使用 Discord `retry_after`，否则指数退避\n\n**Telegram：**\n- 在 transient 错误时重试（429 / timeout / connect/reset/closed / temporarily unavailable）\n- 优先使用 `retry_after`，否则指数退避\n- Markdown 解析错误不重试，降级为纯文本\n\n### 35.4 配置\n\n```json5\n{\n  channels: {\n    telegram: {\n      retry: {\n        attempts: 3,\n        minDelayMs: 400,\n        maxDelayMs: 30000,\n        jitter: 0.1,\n      },\n    },\n    discord: {\n      retry: {\n        attempts: 3,\n        minDelayMs: 500,\n        maxDelayMs: 30000,\n        jitter: 0.1,\n      },\n    },\n  },\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 36. SOUL.md 人格撰写指南\n\n### 36.1 定位\n\n`SOUL.md` 是 OpenClaw 注入人格的官方位置，对话中有真实影响。如果 Agent 听起来平淡/圆滑/企业化，通常是这个文件需要改。\n\n### 36.2 应该放什么\n\n- **tone**（语气）\n- **opinions**（观点）\n- **brevity**（简洁）\n- **humor**（幽默）\n- **boundaries**（边界）\n- **default level of bluntness**（默认直接程度）\n\n### 36.3 不应该放什么\n\n- 人生故事\n- changelog\n- 安全策略 dump\n- 没有行为效果的巨型氛围文字墙\n\n**原则：短胜过长，锋利胜过模糊。**\n\n### 36.4 为什么有效\n\n符合 OpenAI 的 prompt 工程指导：高层级行为/语气/目标/示例应放在高优先级指令层，而非埋在 user turn 里。\n\n---\n\n## 附录：关键文件路径"}]}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":74062,"output":2934,"cacheRead":21036,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":98032,"cost":{"input":0.022218599999999998,"output":0.0035207999999999997,"cacheRead":0.0012621599999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.027001559999999997}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776337045945,"responseId":"062ff395bef700ac64afe891795c5b3a"}}
