{"type":"message","id":"9935d73b","parentId":"a68d864c","timestamp":"2026-04-16T11:17:31.358Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see the issue - there's a `\"memory-lancedb\"` entry and then `\"memory-core\"` entry. I need to remove the memory-lancedb entry. But also I see there's a `\"feishu\"` entry with just `\"config\": {}`. Let me carefully plan the edits.\n\nThe current structure around memory-lancedb and memory-core:\n```\n      \"memory-lancedb\": {\n        \"enabled\": true,\n        ...\n      },\n      \"memory-core\": {\n        \"enabled\": true,\n        \"config\": {\n          \"dreaming\": {\n            \"enabled\": true\n          }\n        }\n      },\n```\n\nI need to remove the memory-lancedb block and add active-memory after memory-core.\n\n\nSo my edits are: remove the memory-lancedb entry with its comma, then insert the active-memory configuration after the memory-core block closes.","thinkingSignature":"a254efe712b483219b5a9cb0892f890ba70c1626401e4ab1ca3f152ea4a10379"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_6176t70lscco_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 -c \"\nwith open('/home/ai/.openclaw/openclaw.json') as f:\n    content = f.read()\n# Find memory-core block ending\nidx = content.find('\\\"memory-core\\\"')\nprint(repr(content[idx-20:idx+500]))\n\" 2>&1"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":47920,"output":259,"cacheRead":18725,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":66904,"cost":{"input":0.014376,"output":0.00031079999999999997,"cacheRead":0.0011235,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0158103}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776338244616,"responseId":"062ff844995f3a6c9085eab9a1c0054f"}}
