{"type":"message","id":"49d3b00e","parentId":"111def51","timestamp":"2026-04-16T11:20:48.028Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"- `172.23.96.1:11434` — Ollama is accessible at this address ✅ and it has `bge-m3:latest` model which is a great embedding model!\n- `127.0.0.1:11434` — no response\n\nSo the Ollama at `172.23.96.1:11434` is accessible and has the `bge-m3:latest` embedding model. This is the same setup that was previously used by the memory-lancedb config.\n\nNow I need to configure `agents.defaults.memorySearch` to use this Ollama endpoint. I need to add this to the openclaw.json.","thinkingSignature":"1c73f43edf6f959a47585442a692364b8733de35e8cba66be69fdb30cc9ff338"},{"type":"text","text":"Ollama 在 `172.23.96.1:11434` 完全可以联通，且已经装了 `bge-m3:latest`（ embedding 模型）。现在把这个配回去：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_8ga997n9f4zp_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 << 'EOF'\nimport json\n\npath = '/home/ai/.openclaw/openclaw.json'\nwith open(path) as f:\n    d = json.load(f)\n\n# Add memorySearch config to agents.defaults\nd.setdefault('agents', {}).setdefault('defaults', {})\nd['agents']['defaults']['memorySearch'] = {\n    \"provider\": \"ollama\",\n    \"model\": \"bge-m3\",\n    \"baseUrl\": \"http://172.23.96.1:11434/v1\"\n}\n\nwith open(path, 'w') as f:\n    json.dump(d, f, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False)\n\nprint(\"Done\")\n\n# Verify\nwith open(path) as f:\n    d2 = json.load(f)\nprint(json.dumps(d2['agents']['defaults'].get('memorySearch'), indent=2))\nEOF"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":53489,"output":378,"cacheRead":21798,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":75665,"cost":{"input":0.0160467,"output":0.00045359999999999997,"cacheRead":0.00130788,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.01780818}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776338439499,"responseId":"062ff90684c555de7d9bcdbb6668e558"}}
