{"type":"message","id":"2c743e24","parentId":"dee3206a","timestamp":"2026-04-16T11:26:11.062Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"From the log I can see:\n\n1. **Active Memory is still timing out** - `status=timeout elapsedMs=28453 summaryChars=0` - it's taking 28 seconds (longer than the 15s timeout config). This is a problem. The memory search seems to be configured correctly (ollama), but the Active Memory sub-agent itself is timing out.\n\n2. **No more memory-lancedb config warning** - good, the warning is gone.\n\n3. **Memory search provider is now ollama** - confirmed working, vector ready.\n\nThe issue with Active Memory timeout seems to be that even though the embedding provider is now configured, the Active Memory sub-agent itself is still timing out at 28 seconds. \n\nSo it looks like the memory backend is probably working fine, but the Active Memory agent running the search is taking longer than the configured 15-second timeout and then giving up.","thinkingSignature":"f4962320cd367b5f032aec284f99762058090eb8342d4d4f10594b10fda59d56"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_mfn09m9gfc3c_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"~/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/bin/openclaw memory search \"hello\" 2>&1 | head -20"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":57053,"output":239,"cacheRead":21798,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":79090,"cost":{"input":0.0171159,"output":0.0002868,"cacheRead":0.00130788,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.01871058}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776338761991,"responseId":"062ffa4958e156b0e08e47274c9eff28"}}
