{"type":"message","id":"04a415a5","parentId":"31e92ba0","timestamp":"2026-04-16T11:26:42.923Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The memory search is working - it's returning results. The issue is that the Active Memory sub-agent is taking too long to process results. \n\nLet me look at the log to understand why Active Memory is still timing out even after fixing the memory search. The timeout is 15s but it ran for 28s and got killed. This suggests the issue is in the Active Memory sub-agent's execution time, not the memory search itself.\n\nActually, looking more carefully at the log:\n```\n\"active-memory: agent=main session=agent:main:main activeProvider=minimax activeModel=MiniMax-M2.7 done status=timeout elapsedMs=28453 summaryChars=0\"\n\n\n```\n\nThe timeout is 15000ms (15s), but it ran for 28453ms (28s). This means the sub-agent didn't respect the timeout and ran longer. The issue might be that the sub-agent itself is slow (model inference is slow), not the memory search.\n\nWait - `elapsedMs=28453` means it ran for 28 seconds, which is longer than the configured 15 second timeout. So the sub-agent started, the timeout fired, but it kept running anyway until it finally returned with no summary and a timeout status.\n\nThe memory search is working fine - it's the Active Memory sub-agent that's timing out. This could be because the model itself is slow to respond, or there's something else stalling the sub-agent's execution.\n\nLooking at the config, it uses MiniMax-M2.7 with a 15 second timeout, but the sub-agent ran for 28 seconds before timing out. That's suspicious - either the timeout setting isn't being respected properly, or the sub-agent is getting stuck somewhere in its execution.\n\nThe recent user message about being asked \"你是谁\" suggests the memory search is working fine, so the problem is likely that the model response itself is taking too long. The sub-agent could be failing to connect to MiniMax-M2.7 or the model is just being slow with the memory search results.\n\nThe status=timeout with elapsedMs=28453 (28 seconds) indicates the timeout isn't being enforced properly - it should only run for 15 seconds max. So the issue is either the timeout config isn't being applied, or the sub-agent is stuck waiting on something else.\n\nI need to look at the actual memory search configuration and verify what baseUrl is being used, since it might have been stripped down during a previous config cleanup.\n\n```\nbaseUrl: \"http://172.23.96.1:11434/v1\"\n```","thinkingSignature":"a4ea3b70ac3d0f46568f445e3c025ee62e9c2fd0ffcf738b0f81ab68b8a69cd6"},{"type":"text","text":"Memory search 本身是通的。让我看看 Active Memory 最新的超时日志：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_dyi1c8ijdlwg_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /tmp/openclaw/openclaw-2026-04-16.log | grep -E \"active-memory\" | tail -5 | python3 -c \"\nimport sys, json\nfor line in sys.stdin:\n    try:\n        d = json.loads(line)\n        msg = d.get('1','')\n        t = d.get('time','')\n        print(t, msg[:200])\n    except:\n        print(line[:200])\n\" 2>&1"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":57666,"output":657,"cacheRead":21798,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":80121,"cost":{"input":0.0172998,"output":0.0007884,"cacheRead":0.00130788,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.019396080000000003}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776338784902,"responseId":"062ffa60f460e0711251985f91f8710d"}}
