{"type":"message","id":"bc07d053","parentId":"79535645","timestamp":"2026-04-16T11:27:06.570Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The latest run:\n- `activeModel=MiniMax-M2.7` (the current session model)\n- `start timeoutMs=15000 queryChars=673` - so the timeout is 15s, query is 673 chars\n- `done status=timeout elapsedMs=28453` - took 28s and still timed out\n\nThe queryChars=673 means the context sent to the Active Memory sub-agent is 673 characters. That's not large. But the timeout is 15s and it's running 28s.\n\nThe problem seems to be that the Active Memory sub-agent IS actually getting the model response, but it's taking very long because MiniMax-M2.7 might be slow in this context. \n\nOr maybe the sub-agent keeps retrying or doing multiple rounds. Actually wait - if the status is \"timeout\" but elapsedMs=28453 > timeoutMs=15000, that means the timeout wasn't respected and the sub-agent ran to completion anyway, returning a timeout status.\n\nSo the sub-agent actually finished its work, but only reported back after the timeout had already fired - which suggests either the timeout is set too aggressively, or there's something causing the sub-agent to take much longer than expected even though it eventually completes successfully.\n\nLooking at the elapsed time of 28 seconds for a 673-character context, that's unusually slow for MiniMax-M2.7, pointing to either network latency or the sub-agent getting stuck in multiple retries before finally succeeding.\n\nBut there's a more immediate problem: the Active Memory config has `baseUrl` set to Ollama at `172.23.96.1:11434`, but the tool call is showing `MiniMax-M2.7` as the model. This suggests the Active Memory sub-agent is routing to MiniMax instead of using the configured Ollama endpoint, which means the baseUrl setting might not be taking effect for this particular sub-agent call. The elapsed time of 28 seconds for a 673-character context with MiniMax suggests the model might be hitting cold start latency or the connection is slow, even though it should typically respond faster. The core issue seems to be that the sub-agent is running too slowly to complete within the timeout window, so I need to either increase the timeout threshold or investigate why MiniMax is taking so long for such a short context. The sub-agent's actual work (generating a summary from memory results) might be slow with MiniMax-M2.7. \n\nA pragmatic fix: increase timeout to 30s and see if it completes successfully. If MiniMax is just slow, this will help. If there's a deeper issue, the increased timeout will let us see a successful run or a more informative error.\n\nFor now, let me just increase the timeout to 30 seconds. 15 seconds seems too tight for a model inference call in this environment.\n\nLooking at the bigger picture, the memory search itself works and returns results, but Active Memory sub-agent is taking 28 seconds with a 15-second timeout. Increasing to 30 seconds should help. But I need to verify that the baseUrl configuration is actually being respected—it's currently set to `http://172.23.96.1:11434/v1`, but the active memory might be using a different model configuration.\n\nLet me increase the timeout and see if the sub-agent can complete successfully.","thinkingSignature":"a483b6f86d641eb0b4a518532f5746981895ca1b7fc5af129a59adbb487a27b1"},{"type":"text","text":"情况清楚了：\n\n- Memory search ✅ 正常（Ollama bge-m3，0 报错）\n- Active Memory ❌ 超时：配置 15s，实际跑 28s 才完成\n- 本质：MiniMax-M2.7 在这个上下文里响应慢，15s 不够\n\n把超时放宽到 30s 让他跑完：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_y0qx9ak4oapu_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 << 'EOF'\nimport json\n\npath = '/home/ai/.openclaw/openclaw.json'\nwith open(path) as f:\n    d = json.load(f)\n\nd['plugins']['entries']['active-memory']['config']['timeoutMs'] = 30000\n\nwith open(path, 'w') as f:\n    json.dump(d, f, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False)\n\nprint(\"Done. New timeout:\", d['plugins']['entries']['active-memory']['config']['timeoutMs'])\nEOF"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":58582,"output":885,"cacheRead":21798,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":81265,"cost":{"input":0.0175746,"output":0.001062,"cacheRead":0.00130788,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.01994448}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776338803354,"responseId":"062ffa7247ce5d80ccb3717e635bde3b"}}
