{"type":"message","id":"627256f4","parentId":"6ed460d4","timestamp":"2026-04-16T11:27:15.667Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Wait, I need to think about this more carefully. Looking at the log again:\n- `activeModel=MiniMax-M2.7` - the AM sub-agent is using MiniMax\n- `activeProvider=minimax` - from the minimax profile\n\nBut the memorySearch uses Ollama bge-m3 for embeddings. The AM sub-agent itself uses MiniMax-M2.7 for generating the summary from memory search results. 28 seconds for that seems really long.\n\nActually, let me look at this from a completely different angle. Maybe the issue is that the AM sub-agent is getting stuck connecting to MiniMax at all. \n\nIf MiniMax itself is responding fine elsewhere, then something about how the AM sub-agent is configured to reach it must be the bottleneck.\n\nThe memory search returns results successfully in about 4 seconds, but the sub-agent takes 28 seconds total—so it's likely spending most of that time waiting on MiniMax to generate the summary, or there's significant overhead in bootstrapping the sub-agent itself. Since this is running under the main session's context, MiniMax should be configured and available, but maybe the AM sub-agent's network connection to MiniMax is the real constraint here.","thinkingSignature":"052fbf15441df1ce231af05a24fb6c0ec8a99c872608fe45396aac8dd76b78f5"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_qlauvxc33d11_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"systemctl --user restart openclaw-gateway 2>&1 && echo \"restarted\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":59491,"output":288,"cacheRead":21798,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":81577,"cost":{"input":0.0178473,"output":0.0003456,"cacheRead":0.00130788,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.019500780000000002}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776338827103,"responseId":"062ffa8af3c9a3b2fbd8e1ae8c9694c7"}}
