{"type":"message","id":"c7abbae2","parentId":"b4d4d9ff","timestamp":"2026-04-16T11:29:03.746Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The problem persists even with 30s timeout. The Active Memory sub-agent is consistently timing out after ~28-29 seconds with MiniMax-M2.7. This means the model itself is slow to respond in this context.\n\nThe issue isn't the timeout value. The Active Memory sub-agent uses the same model as the main agent (MiniMax-M2.7), and it's taking ~28 seconds just to respond to the memory search query. This is very slow.\n\nOptions:\n1. Use a faster model for Active Memory (e.g., gemini-3-flash as fallback, or use ollama/qwen2.5:14b)\n\n\n2. Configure `modelFallback` in Active Memory to use a faster local model instead\n3. The real culprit might be cold start overhead on MiniMax-M2.7, so switching to a local model like Ollama could eliminate that latency\n\nSince `bge-m3` is already configured and running locally, the bottleneck is clearly the MiniMax model itself. I should check whether the queryChars value has changed or if the 30s timeout is still being hit at the same point.\n\nEven with the increased timeout, it's consistently hitting 28-29 seconds, which points to an overhead issue rather than a timeout configuration problem. The query length is stable around 632-673 chars, so that's not the variable. The real issue is that MiniMax-M2.7 takes nearly 30 seconds to respond to this particular task, which suggests I should either use a faster model as the Active Memory fallback or investigate what's causing the slowdown on the MiniMax side.\n\nI'm checking the Active Memory configuration to see if a model is explicitly set or if it's inheriting from the session. Since `model` isn't configured in the plugin config, it should be using the session model (MiniMax-M2.7), but maybe the modelFallback parameter would help route to a faster option instead.\n\nLooking at the fallback chain, even specifying `google/gemini-3-flash` won't work without an API key or configured provider. Since Ollama is already set up locally with qwen2.5:14b available and responsive, I could configure the modelFallback to use that instead, which would give us a fast local option without external dependencies.","thinkingSignature":"1747c5c9040fb24b5f74d65a02e6fb903f3f5f259cfc745146dae84916c4265f"},{"type":"text","text":"问题不在超时值。30s 一样跑满，说明 MiniMax-M2.7 在这个场景下响应本身就需要 28s+。\n\n换本地 fast 模型当 fallback 最根本：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_s8lunckmsa6r_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 << 'EOF'\nimport json\n\npath = '/home/ai/.openclaw/openclaw.json'\nwith open(path) as f:\n    d = json.load(f)\n\ncfg = d['plugins']['entries']['active-memory']['config']\ncfg['modelFallback'] = \"ollama/qwen2.5:14b\"\ncfg['timeoutMs'] = 30000\n\nwith open(path, 'w') as f:\n    json.dump(d, f, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False)\n\nprint(\"Done:\", json.dumps(cfg, indent=2))\nEOF"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":58681,"output":643,"cacheRead":21798,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":81122,"cost":{"input":0.0176043,"output":0.0007716,"cacheRead":0.00130788,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.01968378}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776338926477,"responseId":"062ffaedccea5876db3fd902b8691460"}}
