{"type":"message","id":"671c4ebb","parentId":"979db60e","timestamp":"2026-04-16T11:33:31.218Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking why their messages take a while to be sent/delivered. This could be related to queue behavior, or it could be related to the Active Memory timeout situation we just fixed. Let me check the message queue settings and also check recent logs for any delays.\n\nActually, thinking about this - the user might be experiencing this in WebChat or a specific channel. Let me check the queue configuration and recent logs to see what's happening with message flow.\n\nActually, let me first understand what channel they're using. They said \"发出去的信息\" - sent messages. This could be the Control UI / webchat itself. The delay could be from:\n1. Active Memory blocking (the old 28s timeout we fixed)\n\n\n2. The queue mode\n3. Some other processing\n\nI should look at the logs to see what's causing the delay.","thinkingSignature":"414f375d20b3ab147118dca6917c35731e6e0bafc749af27261dbc9a5a2c75d9"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_kf07ud7wb7vm_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.openclaw/openclaw.json | python3 -c \"\nimport json,sys\nd=json.load(sys.stdin)\nprint('queue mode:', json.dumps(d.get('messages',{}).get('queue',{}), indent=2))\nprint('gateway loopback:', d.get('gateway',{}).get('bind'))\n\" 2>&1"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_kf07ud7wb7vm_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /tmp/openclaw/openclaw-2026-04-16.log | grep -E \"(queue|collect|steer|delay|blocked)\" | tail -10 | python3 -c \"\nimport sys, json\nfor line in sys.stdin:\n    try:\n        d = json.loads(line)\n        t = d.get('time','')[:19]\n        print(t, str(d.get('1',''))[:120])\n    except:\n        print(line[:120])\n\" 2>&1"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":58,"output":390,"cacheRead":21798,"cacheWrite":61708,"totalTokens":83954,"co