{"type":"message","id":"acd1de24","parentId":"412669d2","timestamp":"2026-04-16T11:33:54.943Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see `lane wait exceeded` messages - these indicate that the per-session lane is waiting for the previous agent run to complete before processing the next message. The `waitedMs` values are very large (hundreds of seconds in some cases). This is the session lane serialization.\n\nFor example:\n- `waitedMs=57901` = waited 57 seconds for the previous run to finish\n- `waitedMs=340916` = waited 340 seconds (5.7 minutes!)\n\nThis explains the delay. The per-session lane is serializing messages - if one message is being processed (agent running), the next message has to wait.\n\nBut wait, the most recent ones are from today. \n\nLooking at the timestamps more carefully, I'm noticing a pattern of extremely long wait times throughout the day - ranging from 57 seconds up to over 11 minutes. The most recent entries show waits of 224 seconds and 378 seconds, which is way too long for a typical messaging flow. The question is whether this is a configuration issue with how the queue is set up, or if there's something about the recent messages that explains why they're taking so long to process.\n\nActually, the \"lane wait exceeded\" messages are likely a normal part of the system - they fire when an incoming message hits a lane that's already processing something. But these numbers are suspicious: `waitedMs=730540` is over 12 minutes, which is way longer than any reasonable model timeout. I'm thinking the 3103 scorer might be the culprit here, or maybe even the Active Memory blocking subagent, since it uses the same LLM as the main agent and could be holding up the queue while waiting for a response.\n\nWait, I'm realizing these wait times might not actually be delays in sending - they could just be showing how long the system waited before logging the \"exceeded\" message. Let me reconsider what the user is actually experiencing: are they seeing their message sit in the queue before it gets sent to the model, or is there an actual delivery delay after the model responds? I need to ask them to clarify what's happening, but first I should check if the current timing in the logs is reasonable by looking at the most recent request.","thinkingSignature":"f4dddedc8263d6bc8ce393930a730e8926b37546d16fb98901cd0c20b90e087a"},{"type":"text","text":"看到问题了。日志里有大量 `lane wait exceeded`：\n\n```\nwaitedMs=730540   ← 等了 12 分钟\nwaitedMs=340916   ← 等了 5.7 分钟  \nwaitedMs=378357   ← 等了 6.3 分钟\n```\n\n这是 **per-session lane 串行化**导致的——上一个 agent 任务没跑完，新消息只能排队等着。但这个等待时间太长了，说明模型本身响应很慢。\n\n让我看最新的等待情况：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_i5c510icmthq_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /tmp/openclaw/openclaw-2026-04-16.log | grep \"lane wait exceeded\" | tail -5 | python3 -c \"\nimport sys, json\nfor line in sys.stdin:\n    try:\n        d = json.loads(line)\n        t = d.get('time','')[:19]\n        m = str(d.get('1',''))\n        print(t, m[:200])\n    except:\n        print(line[:200])\n\" 2>&1"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":62512,"output":679,"cacheRead":21798,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":84989,"cost":{"input":0.0187536,"output":0.0008148,"cacheRead":0.00130788,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.02087628}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776339211964,"responseId":"062ffc0b75f2be4b54efa5fb325d3f22"}}
