{"type":"message","id":"181fc992","parentId":"3e8647e3","timestamp":"2026-04-16T11:36:09.769Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see only `active-memory` starts in this log. There are no `agent_command` entries visible, which means the actual main agent hasn't been processing messages. \n\nThe active-memory is running, but the actual main agent reply is not happening. This suggests the messages from the user are going through the scoring/classification and then... nothing. The agent isn't generating a response.\n\nWait - this log might be filtered. Let me look at the raw log more broadly for what happens when the user sends a message. Let me look at the ephemeral file for the current session since those have the scoring data.\n\nActually, looking at the timestamps:\n- 19:35:06 - active-memory start\n- 19:35:29 - active-memory done (elapsedMs=2247)\n\nThat's only 2.2 seconds. The active memory is now fast! And it's completing with status=empty.\n \nBut the user's saying messages are still slow, which means the problem might be elsewhere. Let me trace what happens after active-memory finishes - I need to find the main agent's response generation step. The user could be seeing delay either from the full round-trip (score + classify + active-memory + agent + response) or from something blocking before the agent even starts.\n\nLooking at the 19:35 active-memory cycle - it took about 23 seconds total with a 30000ms timeout set, but only ran for 2.2 seconds. That timeout suggests something else was taking too long, maybe the model itself was slow to respond. The real question is whether the user is seeing this 2-second active-memory overhead on top of whatever else is happening, or if there's a separate bottleneck in the agent response generation itself. So the total time from user message to reply is scoring (~0ms), classify (~0ms), active-memory (~2-25s depending on context), then the actual agent inference. The active-memory is just a pre-processing step, so if the user is experiencing slowness, it's likely the main agent model that's taking 25+ seconds to generate a response. Let me check if there's a running agent task right now.","thinkingSignature":"5f467b7dfc7e23039f992cb595c9ca9025fc7a628c2f67d6f7b9f65abde3e7d6"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_dgwwc5hgfgxd_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"~/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/bin/openclaw tasks 2>&1 | head -30"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":68586,"output":483,"cacheRead":21798,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":90867,"cost":{"input":0.020575799999999998,"output":0.0005796,"cacheRead":0.00130788,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.02246328}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776339352436,"responseId":"062ffc976afe812f43066cd0590dfd9c"}}
