{"type":"message","id":"8cdc1a69","parentId":"9f24e1e0","timestamp":"2026-04-16T11:36:48.957Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The tasks look mostly old (from today around 13-15:39). No active tasks running. Let me check if there's a currently running agent task.\n\nActually, looking at the logs again - the Control UI polling is showing up as \"handshake timeout\" because the WebSocket connections from the Control UI are trying to connect to port 3102 which is the gateway's RPC port, not the WebSocket control UI port. Wait, port 3102 IS the gateway port. The Control UI connects to the gateway via WebSocket.\n\nActually the \"handshake timeout\" messages are from other clients trying to connect to the gateway and timing out during the WebSocket handshake. \n\nSo the Control UI is successfully connecting with those `⇄ res ✓ sessions.list` responses, but there are also many failed connections from other clients timing out. Looking at the message flow, it seems the user's message goes through active-memory then nothing - the main agent isn't generating responses. The \"slow\" they're experiencing might be that the message enters the system but the reply takes time, or they're seeing the active-memory overhead on top of the actual response time.\n\nWith active-memory enabled on the main agent, every message now carries roughly 2-25 seconds of overhead before the main agent even starts. That's a significant latency hit. Since active-memory is configured for the \"main\" agent and the Control UI session runs through that same main agent, this overhead is affecting their experience. But the user specifically said messages are sending slowly, not that replies are slow - which suggests something might be wrong with the message submission itself rather than the response generation.\n\nLooking at the recent logs around 19:35, active-memory was taking about 23 seconds with a 30-second timeout, which is the bottleneck. The simplest fix would be to disable active-memory temporarily to see if that resolves the sending delay. Alternatively, I could reduce the timeout further or switch the queryMode to \"message\" instead of \"recent\" to reduce the processing overhead. Let me check the current active-memory configuration to see what queryMode is actually set to. so the delay compounds with each step. I should just recommend disabling active-memory since it's introducing too much latency, and we can revisit it once the memory system has meaningful content to work with.","thinkingSignature":"4716d0210af02a324840e0e1f8da08d75f567099d3d54ad55cae18c8155288b6"},{"type":"text","text":"找到原因了。看这条线：\n\n```\n19:35:06 active-memory start  (queryChars=697)\n19:35:29 active-memory done   elapsedMs=2247 (2.2秒，之前最慢到28秒)\n```\n\nActive Memory 每次消息要先跑一个 2-25 秒的 sub-agent（搜记忆），然后才到主 agent 生成回复。**这条链路是串行的**，你感受到的\"发消息慢\"实际上是：\n\n```\n你的消息 → 2-25秒 Active Memory sub-agent → 主 agent 回复\n           ↑ 这里在等\n```\n\n而且这个 session 现在 memory 是空的（`status=empty`），Active Memory 每次跑完返回 0 字符，等于白跑了 2-25 秒。\n\n**建议：暂时关掉 Active Memory**，因为记忆库是空的，它现在只会拖速度。等记忆积累一些之后再开才有意义。\n\n要关吗？"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":69955,"output":651,"cacheRead":21798,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":92404,"cost":{"input":0.020986499999999998,"output":0.0007812,"cacheRead":0.00130788,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.02307558}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776339382041,"responseId":"062ffcb6bfb564dd103617babe7f033f"}}
