{"type":"message","id":"3e83544e","parentId":"ac7b907e","timestamp":"2026-04-16T12:09:11.477Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Looking at the sessions output, I can see the sessions are using different models:\n- Some use MiniMax-M2.7 (most)\n- Some use qwen2.5:14b (older ones)\n\nThe session `agent:fast_agent:main` is listed as \"1h ago\" with MiniMax-M2.7. That seems to be the currently active one for the fast_agent.\n\nBut wait - the main session in the sessions list doesn't seem to show recent activity for the \"main\" agent. Let me look more carefully...\n\nActually, I notice the sessions listed are all from `agent:fast_agent:...`. The `agent:main:...` sessions don't appear in this list. \n\nThere might be a distinction between the main OpenClaw session and the fast_agent's sessions, or the main agent's sessions are so active that they don't show up in this truncated view. The fact that messages are still slow after removing active-memory suggests the bottleneck is actually the MiniMax-M2.7 model response time itself, which was previously hidden by the active-memory overhead.\n\nBut that doesn't quite fit—before active-memory was added, messages were reportedly fast, so something else must have changed. Let me reconsider: the lane wait logs from earlier in the day (15:44-17:38 timeframes) show extremely long wait times ranging from 3 to 730 seconds, which is suspicious. These might be lingering in the log file from older entries, or the gateway's been running continuously since this morning. The real question is what's causing the slowdown right now.\n\nLooking at the session list, most are marked as \"1h ago\" or older, which seems off if the user is actively using it. I'm also noticing something odd with the fast_agent sessions—there's a session ID \"9adddcac-c8eb-4987-b729-ab5afef1c731\" with think:adaptive showing as \"1h ago\", but earlier today around 19:03-19:09 there was recent activity. That timing doesn't add up. Let me reconsider the user's actual situation: they've confirmed messages are still slow even after removing active-memory, they're using the webchat Control UI, and the gateway is performing normal operations like sessions.list and node.list with typical latencies around 100-200ms. The sessions.list command itself is taking a long time to complete.\n\nThe gateway is clearly struggling—commands are timing out, sessions are slow to list, and recent sessions aren't showing up at all. This could mean an agent task is running and blocking new requests, or there's an abnormal load causing queuing. I should check the gateway's current load and see if there are any stuck or running tasks that would explain why new messages are being queued.","thinkingSignature":"2dd8c4257479541ccc9825cedfc460de84e66a60d4a621dcf00951745effbe7d"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_iibjtc3ygpgb_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"uptime; free -h | head -2; echo \"---\"; cat /proc/loadavg"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":79093,"output":605,"cacheRead":21798,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":101496,"cost":{"input":0.0237279,"output":0.000726,"cacheRead":0.00130788,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.02576178}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776341329804,"responseId":"06300451421624270f7a0d8dd3aa77b8"}}
