{"type":"message","id":"ef171d33","parentId":"da30bb24","timestamp":"2026-04-16T12:10:09.588Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Gateway is still writing logs and active. The sessions.list is taking 131ms which is normal. The handshake timeouts are just the Control UI polling connections timing out.\n\nSo the gateway is healthy. The issue must be that messages from the user are taking a long time to get a response. This is likely because the main agent is busy with a task, and new messages are queued.\n\nBut I haven't seen any recent \"lane wait\" logs. Maybe the user's session IS the \"agent:fast_agent:main\" session, and it's just that MiniMax-M2.7 is slow to respond (20-30 seconds for the model itself, plus any processing time).\n \nLooking back at the sessions list output, the `agent:fast_agent:main 1h ago MiniMax-M2.7 think:adaptive` entry suggests that about an hour ago, someone sent a message using the MiniMax-M2.7 model with adaptive thinking enabled, and we're still waiting for the response.\n\nThe think:adaptive setting is likely contributing to the slowdown, though MiniMax-M2.7 itself is probably just inherently slow. I should explain this to the user and ask them to test sending a new message now to see if the Control UI is actually responsive. But I also need to reconsider the timestamp—if sessions.list ran at 20:07 and returned sessions with \"1h ago\" for the fast_agent:main session, that means the last activity was around 19:07, which is odd given the 20+ minute gap between messages and the Gateway restart at 19:41.\n\nThe timing suggests the user sent messages during the 19:41 restart window, and after the restart those sessions reconnected but have been processing slowly ever since. The core issue is that the `think:adaptive` model setting is enabled, which adds extra thinking time on top of an already slow base model, and without active-memory providing context, the model has to think more. The session appears \"stuck\" because each message takes 20-30 seconds just for the model to generate a response.\n\nSince the Gateway restarted at 19:41 and the user is reporting slowness, any sessions created before that restart would have had their state reloaded, which could be compounding the problem. I should ask the user to send a fresh message right now so I can see the actual timing in real time.","thinkingSignature":"32f5f9e23cd7ac82a766791f5c25e7f14deedac6d66b4d67a2f18605de314fdd"},{"type":"text","text":"Gateway 本身是健康的（sessions.list 130ms 正常，没有新的 lane wait）。但 sessions 里显示 `agent:fast_agent:main` 上次活动是 1h ago，说明那个 session 的最后一条消息跑了很久没回来。\n\n**核心原因很可能是这个**：`think:adaptive` 在 MiniMax-M2.7 上本身就是额外开销——模型边推理边思考，比单纯回复慢很多。\n\n你现在发一条新消息，我实时看日志确认耗时：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_1o2bhyfwlrtu_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"tail -f /tmp/openclaw/openclaw-2026-04-16.log | grep -E \"(agent_command|embedded.*start|embedded.*done|20:[1-3])\" | python3 -c \"\nimport sys, json\nfor line in sys.stdin:\n    try:\n        d = json.loads(line)\n        t = d.get('time','')[:19]\n        msg = str(d.get('1', d.get('0','')))[:140]\n        print(t, msg)\n    except:\n        print(line.strip()[:140])\n\" &\nLOGPID=$!\nsleep 45\nkill $LOGPID 2>/dev/null\nwait $LOGPID 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":80909,"output":746,"cacheRead":21798,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":103453,"cost":{"input":0.024272699999999998,"output":0.0008952,"cacheRead":0.00130788,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.026475779999999997}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776341382481,"responseId":"06300486dbbc02b6184313bcf3c5ceb8"}}
