{"type":"message","id":"a0dc2bca","parentId":"1abdd49a","timestamp":"2026-04-16T12:11:54.877Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user says this slowness didn't happen before the update. This is a significant clue. Before the update, they were on v2026.4.9 and after updating to v2026.4.14, this issue appeared.\n\nLet me think about what changed in v2026.4.10+ that could cause this:\n\n1. **Active Memory** - This was added in v2026.4.10. Even if configured correctly, it runs before every main agent reply, adding latency. But I had it disabled/deleted...\n\nActually wait - the user said they deleted the active-memory config. But was the plugin still enabled in the plugin list? When I added the active-memory config, the plugin changed from \"disabled\" to \"enabled\". When the user deleted the config, it went back to not being in entries... but the plugin binary is still loaded in memory from the plugin system.\n \nBut the user manually removed the active-memory config entry entirely, so the plugin shouldn't be running at all. The real issue might be something else that changed in v2026.4.10+ - maybe something in the scoring/classifier system or another component that's now running by default.\n\nActually, I'm realizing the core question: if the user hasn't configured or enabled anything new yet the system is slower after upgrading, then something in the upgrade itself must be introducing the overhead. The question is what specifically in v2026.4.10+ is consuming resources or adding latency by default.\n\nWait, I should check if the v8 scoring and classification services are being called more frequently now, or if there's something about the thinking mode that's consuming extra tokens and causing slower responses.","thinkingSignature":"edd1484518e1e6c9e88c50a8a2932a92c14e926445ab20d3b001238cddcb712f"},{"type":"text","text":"这个信息很关键——升级前没有，升级后有。说明是 v2026.4.14 里的某个变化在影响。\n\n让我排查几个可能性：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_bz7v3vwaaxrf_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /tmp/openclaw/openclaw-2026-04-16.log | grep -E \"(20:09|20:10|20:11)\" | grep -v \"handshake timeout\" | tail -20 | python3 -c \"\nimport sys, json\nfor line in sys.stdin:\n    try:\n        d = json.loads(line)\n        t = d.get('time','')[:19]\n        msg = str(d.get('1', d.get('0','')))[:120]\n        print(t, msg)\n    except:\n        print(line.strip()[:120])\n\" 2>&1"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":50,"output":524,"cacheRead":674,"cacheWrite":97990,"totalTokens":99238,"cost":{"input":0.000014999999999999999,"output":0.0006288,"cacheRead":0.00004044,"cacheWrite":0.03674625,"total":0.037430490000000004}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776341495030,"responseId":"063004f692aed056613e1a0738df71b0"}}
