{"type":"message","id":"fabdcb59","parentId":"d6e05e09","timestamp":"2026-04-16T12:12:33.362Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see something very important here:\n\n```\nwebchat connected conn=66b7d058-6897-4066-9159-8cf03349fcd4 remote=::1 client=openclaw-control-ui webchat v2026.4.14\n⇄ res ✗ commands.list 0ms errorCode=INVALID_REQUEST errorMessage=unknown agent id \"main\"\n```\n\nThe error says \"unknown agent id 'main'\". This means the \"main\" agent doesn't exist in the current configuration!\n\nLet me check what agents are configured. Earlier I saw:\n```\nagents list: [\n  {\n    \"id\": \"fast_agent\",\n    \"name\": \"Fast Agent\",\n\n\n```\n\nSo only `fast_agent` and `deep_agent` are defined. There's no agent with id \"main\". But the session `agent:main:main` was running before... and it had `think:adaptive` which is unusual.\n\nThe user is using the webchat and when they connect, it's trying to look up agent \"main\" but it doesn't exist! This could cause issues.\n\nWait, but the current config only has `fast_agent` and `deep_agent` as agents. The `main` agent was using `fast_agent` workspace... or maybe `main` was a reference to the default agent?\n\nActually, I think this is it: when the user runs the main session, it might be using the \"main\" agent ID, but that agent doesn't exist in the config since only `fast_agent` and `deep_agent` are defined. The active configuration is missing the main agent entirely.\n\nBut hold on—if there's no main agent configured, how was the system working at all? Let me check if the upgrade process might have wiped out the agent configuration. Looking back at the output, the agents list only shows `fast_agent` and `deep_agent`, so the main agent really is gone. The question is whether this happened during the upgrade or if it was never properly configured to begin with.\n\nActually, I think the real issue might be that the upgrade from v2026.4.9 to v2026.4.14 is running against a different configuration directory than what's currently set up. If the upgrade was pointed at a different `~/.openclaw/` path, it would explain why the main agent vanished—the old configuration was in a different location. I should verify whether there are multiple openclaw.json files or if the upgrade process accidentally overwrote the main configuration. I'm realizing the issue might be with the OpenClaw configuration itself—if the `agents.defaults` only specifies a workspace without an explicit agent ID, it might default to \"main\", but that agent isn't actually defined in the `agents.list` array. Let me focus on the actual error: the system is reporting an unknown agent ID \"main\", which suggests either the configuration got corrupted during upgrade or there's a mismatch between what the system is trying to use and what's actually defined.\n\nThe user mentioned the Control UI was working fine before the update, so the problem could be that v2026.4.14 handles the \"main\" agent differently—maybe it's now trying to resolve it as a specific agent ID rather than falling back to a default. I should check the upgrade notes to see if there were changes to how the default agent is handled or if the config structure changed in a way that broke existing setups.\n\nWait, I think I found it. The system is saying \"unknown agent id 'main'\" while trying to run `commands.list`, which means it's trying to look up the main agent but can't find it. The current setup only has `fast_agent` and `deep_agent` defined in agents.list, so the main agent is missing. But the user was running sessions under `agent:main:main` before the upgrade, so something about the upgrade process must have corrupted or reset the agent configuration.\n\nActually, maybe the real issue is that the webchat is connecting to the gateway and trying to resume a session, but since the main agent no longer exists in the config, the gateway can't properly route the session. The session state itself might still be intact on disk, but the gateway can't validate the agent ID anymore.\n\nI should clarify with the user whether they're seeing this slowness specifically when resuming an old session from before the upgrade, or if it's happening on completely new sessions. That would help narrow down whether this is a session state compatibility issue or a config problem.","thinkingSignature":"09f31aee0daf97ddc8007dcd0987782c4f5f8666f45fbbca9324e05566976cb3"},{"type":"text","text":"发现重要线索了。看这条日志：\n\n```\n⇄ res ✗ commands.list 0ms errorCode=INVALID_REQUEST errorMessage=unknown agent id \"main\"\n```\n\nControl UI 刚连上来就报错 `unknown agent id \"main\"`——**当前配置里没有 \"main\" 这个 agent**。\n\n当前配置只有 `fast_agent` 和 `deep_agent`，没有 `main`。\n\n这可能是升级后 gateway 行为变了——v2026.4.14 对不存在的 agent 报错更严格，而之前 v2026.4.9 可能静默处理。\n\n**两个问题要确认：**\n\n1. 你发消息慢——是在 Control UI 里发，还是飞书/其他渠道？\n2. \"升级前没这个情况\"——你之前用的 agent ID 是 `main` 吗？\n\n如果之前确实用的是 `main` agent，那现在的配置就少了一个 agent。需要把 `main` 加回去才能正常工作。"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":81576,"output":1091,"cacheRead":18725,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":101392,"cost":{"input":0.0244728,"output":0.0013092,"cacheRead":0.0011235,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0269055}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776341515298,"responseId":"0630050ac87990adaf0fda79a5f967dd"}}
