{"type":"message","id":"85a68494","parentId":"e56f6ba1","timestamp":"2026-04-16T12:14:51.240Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see something very important!\n\nThe logs from 20:11-20:13 ONLY show Control UI polling activity (`sessions.list`, `chat.history`) and `handshake timeout` errors. There are **NO actual inbound user messages** being received by the gateway during this period.\n\nThe `unknown agent id \"main\"` error happened once at 20:11:16, right after the Control UI connected. But since then (20:11-20:13), no user messages have come in.\n\nThe user's complaint about \"messages being slow\" might be that their messages aren't even arriving at the gateway, OR the response isn't making it back.\n\nWait - the user said at 20:11 \"不准关，我要的是解决问题\" and I responded. That response WAS sent through Control UI. So the message round-trip worked for that exchange.\n\n\nThe issue is likely selective - some messages go through while others don't, or there's a delay between when the user sends and when they see a response. The `commands.list` error with \"unknown agent id main\" at 20:11:16 is probably just the Control UI trying to list commands against a non-existent agent, which doesn't necessarily explain the slowness itself. What's striking is that from 20:11 to 20:13, I'm only seeing Control UI's own polling requests (sessions.list every 5 seconds, chat.history) and no actual incoming messages.\n\nLooking at the session list, the \"agent:fast_agent:main\" session is showing as \"1h ago\" for activity, which seems off - I need to figure out if that's a separate fast_agent instance or the main gateway agent, since the gateway itself runs as \"openclaw-gateway\" while the systemd service runs \"openclaw-gateway\".\n\nThe session listing only shows agent sessions (fast_agent, deep_agent), so the main agent's sessions aren't visible in that list. The sessions are sorted by most recent activity, so the \"1h ago\" timestamp is actually the latest activity across all sessions, meaning the user's session hasn't received any messages in an hour. When the user sends a message through Control UI, it must be routing to that fast_agent:main session, so I need to trace what's actually happening to those messages. The gateway seems healthy overall—sessions.list and chat.history are responding quickly at 113-130ms, and there are no error logs. But the user's messages might not be reaching the gateway at all, or the responses aren't making it back. I'm wondering if there's a queuing issue: the Control UI sends a message, it gets queued somewhere, the gateway processes it after some delay, and then the response comes back. Let me check the queue configuration to see if that's where messages are getting stuck.\n\nWait, I need to reconsider the timeline. The user upgraded to 2026.4.14, which added Active Memory as a new feature. That's probably what's causing the slowdown—something about how Active Memory is integrated into the message flow. But when I removed the active-memory config to fix it, the gateway couldn't restart cleanly because the config was invalid, so I had to restart again. The issue might be that removing that plugin changed something fundamental about how messages are being processed, even though it should theoretically be disabled now.\n\nLet me step back and ask the user directly: is the slowness happening when they send a message from Control UI, and does the spinning indicator show up? That would tell me if the bottleneck is in the gateway processing or somewhere else in the pipeline.","thinkingSignature":"c6c7f43c62895f801f82437809949c9e17568cd7cb5ca1857e06e901ebda11d1"},{"type":"text","text":"日志里只看到 Control UI 轮询（sessions.list / chat.history）和 handshake timeout，**没有看到你发的实际消息进来**。\n\n这说明消息可能根本没到达 gateway，或者 gateway 在某个地方把它卡住了。\n\n一个关键问题：你说发消息慢——是从 Control UI 发出后，看到转圈等待时间长，还是点击\"发送\"之后要等很久才出现回复？"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":86142,"output":795,"cacheRead":21798,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":108735,"cost":{"input":0.0258426,"output":0.000954,"cacheRead":0.00130788,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.02810448}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776341659096,"responseId":"063005998e0ca9e19987195a22261106"}}
