{"type":"message","id":"829a9d2e","parentId":"f6294989","timestamp":"2026-04-16T12:18:52.630Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The last active-memory entries are from before 20:00. After the restart at 20:16, there are NO new agent_command or active-memory entries. This means the user's messages after 20:16 are NOT triggering the agent at all.\n\nBut the user said \"发过了，没差别\" - they sent a message and there's no difference (still slow).\n\nThe gateway restart at 20:16 - the main agent was re-added. But there are no agent entries in the log after that. This means:\n1. Either the user's message is NOT reaching the agent at all (routing issue)\n2. Or the gateway is still somehow broken\n\nWait - but sessions.list is working fine. The user is connected via webchat. Let me check if there are any inbound messages after 20:16 in the log that I might have missed.\n\n\nActually, I need to search more broadly for what happens after the user sends a message. Let me look at the complete flow - maybe the message gets queued or stuck before even reaching the agent. The user is using the webchat at localhost:3102, so when they send \"发过了，没差别\", that message should be creating some kind of inbound event in the log. Let me search for anything with a recent timestamp to see what's actually happening when they click send.","thinkingSignature":"bb6df2a0fd9cd54949ed3fc0d91c66dcb9de4b2ccd419f3e0e3fd41de556820c"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_3e08936eb75a4604b9993bce","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /tmp/openclaw/openclaw-2026-04-16.log | grep -E \"(20:18)\" | grep -v \"sessions.list\\|chat.history\\|handshake\" | tail -20 | python3 -c \"\nimport sys, json\nfor line in sys.stdin:\n    try:\n        d = json.loads(line)\n        t = d.get('time','')[:19]\n        msg = str(d.get('1', d.get('0','')))[:130]\n        print(t, msg)\n    except:\n        print(line.strip()[:130])\n\" 2>&1"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","mode