{"type":"message","id":"86dd7852","parentId":"bbd11092","timestamp":"2026-04-16T12:19:04.700Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"No logs at all for 20:18 except the sessions.list polling and handshake timeouts. This strongly suggests the message from the user is NOT even reaching the gateway's agent dispatch system. \n\nThe user's message is going somewhere but not hitting the gateway's agent command handler. The gateway is healthy (it responds to sessions.list in 130ms), but messages aren't triggering agent runs.\n\nWait - I need to look at this differently. The user's message is being typed in the Control UI. The Control UI connects via webchat protocol. The webchat messages go through the gateway. But maybe the Control UI is connecting to the gateway via a specific agent context that changed after the upgrade?\n \nI'm noticing something critical in the logs: at 20:11:16, the Control UI tried to use agent \"main\" but got an `unknown agent id \"main\"` error. I fixed that by adding main back, but now at 20:16:44 it's connecting as `conn=4580a98e...` - which suggests it might be connecting through a different mechanism or context than before.\n\nThe fact that `commands.list` fails with \"unknown agent id main\" is likely why the UI isn't properly dispatching messages to the agent, even though I can see `sessions.list` and `chat.history` working fine. This points to a permissions or routing issue in how the webchat connection handles agent commands.\n\nLooking at the actual timing data from the sessions list, if `think:adaptive` means thinking is enabled, then a 20k token context could add 20-60 seconds of overhead alone. But the user reports this slowness only appeared after upgrading from v2026.4.9 to v2026.4.14, so something specific to that version change is triggering the problem. I should check what model is actually configured in the gateway settings since that's what determines whether thinking gets used in the first place.","thinkingSignature":"250b0dce35baa9a08b1e9adf0f0a16a04a9a40fd42805a9a1ef4240c6a132cfc"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_80d6821577a64869a6be2a7b","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.openclaw/openclaw.json | python3 -c \"\nimport json,sys\nd=json.load(sys.stdin)\nprint('primary model:', d.get('agents',{}).get('defaults',{}).get('model',{}).get('primary','NOT SET'))\nprint('thinking:', d.get('agents',{}).get('defaults',{}).get('thinking','NOT SET'))\nprint()\nprint('channel config:')\nch = d.get('channels',{})\nfor c,v in ch.items():\n    print(f'  {c}: {list(v.keys()) if isinstance(v,dict) else v}')\n\" 2>&1"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":221,"output":546,"cacheRead":110080,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":110847,"cost":{"input":0.0000663,"output":0.0006552,"cacheRead":0.006604799999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.007326299999999999}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776341933044,"responseId":"063006ac579597b2b5dc57f3adc86633"}}
