{"type":"message","id":"12fd8108","parentId":"b63ef7f5","timestamp":"2026-04-16T12:22:11.474Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"There's only ONE chat.send in the logs - from 19:04. And the last one was 89ms which is fast. But the user said they tried sending messages later.\n\nThe most recent chat.send is from 19:04. After 19:04, there's no more chat.send requests. This means either:\n1. The user's messages never got to the gateway at all\n2. Or... something changed after 19:04 that caused messages to not reach gateway\n\nWait - the Control UI reconnects happened around 20:11. Before that the user might have been sending messages but the old connection (a0805f3c) was gone. Let me check when that old connection died.\n\nActually, looking at the sessions list output, I see `direct agent:fast_agent...` and `agent:fast_agent:main`. \n\nSo the user was on fast_agent, not main. But the Control UI is trying to use \"main\" agent - that error happened. Maybe the messages are being sent but they're going somewhere unexpected, or hitting the wrong agent entirely. Or the Control UI is connected but the chat.send requests aren't making it into the logs at all, which would suggest the issue is between the UI and the gateway rather than within the gateway itself.\n\nThe user's complaint about having to wait before seeing their message go out could mean the UI is buffering, or the send itself is slow. Given that I added the \"main\" agent back at 20:16, maybe the 20:18 attempt failed and the user retried at 20:19, but the real problem is that chat.send isn't even showing up in the logs - the gateway isn't receiving the messages at all, which points to something on the frontend blocking or delaying the send operation.\n\nI should step back and look at this more holistically. The \"unknown agent id main\" error in the Control UI suggests the config was missing the main agent, but the user is saying the slowdown started after upgrading without other changes. Maybe there's a mismatch between what the Control UI is configured to use and what's actually in the openclaw.json, or the UI was trying to route to a non-existent agent and timing out, which would explain why adding main back fixed it. But they said it still feels slow, so either something else was the actual bottleneck or there are multiple issues stacked on top of each other. I need to verify whether adding main back actually helped by checking if the `unknown agent id main` error disappeared from the logs.","thinkingSignature":"b00d2cafe674a85e6aef3132c76c73237a9ba590f90d57f653d848006dd6460a"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n日志里只有一个 `chat.send`（19:04），之后完全没有新的消息进来记录。说明你发的消息确实没有到达 gateway。\n\n那个 `unknown agent id \"main\"` 错误还在吗？\n\n```\ncat /tmp/openclaw/openclaw-2026-04-16.log | grep \"unknown agent id\"\n```\n\n这就是关键——如果这个错误还在，说明 gateway 收到消息后因为 agent 不存在而拒绝，你等的就是这个超时。"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":260,"output":602,"cacheRead":111872,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":112734,"cost":{"input":0.000078,"output":0.0007224,"cacheRead":0.006712319999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.007512719999999999}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776342117076,"responseId":"063007651ea15fa4ec1d506ef9cf9c59"}}
