{"type":"message","id":"9664bbcc","parentId":"b63e256e","timestamp":"2026-04-16T12:23:42.267Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The session store is empty `{}` - which means it's using defaults. But the main agent sessions directory has many session files, so it's working. \n\nNow let me think about what's actually happening with the \"slow send\" issue. Since:\n\n1. No chat.send requests appear in the gateway log after 19:04\n2. Gateway is healthy and responsive (sessions.list 100-150ms)\n3. The `unknown agent id \"main\"` error appeared for `commands.list` but NOT for actual message sends\n4. After restart, the Control UI reconnects but no messages come through\n\nWait - I just realized something critical. The messages \"发过了\" (already sent) and \"没差别\" (no difference) are messages FROM the user that I can see in the session. These ARE reaching me. So the issue isn't that messages don't reach gateway - they DO. The user is interacting with me right now!\n \nAh, I see - the user is actually seeing my responses and sending messages, but they're saying their sent messages appear slowly to THEM. So when they click send, there's a delay before the message shows up in their chat interface. That's a different problem - it's not the gateway processing the message, it's the UI displaying it locally.\n\nThe `unknown agent id \"main\"` error on `commands.list` (which failed at 20:11:16 before my restart) might be contributing to this perceived slowness, even though that's a separate command. Let me trace through what actually happened: before the restart, that `commands.list` error would have caused the UI to hang. After I added the main agent and restarted at 20:16, the Control UI reconnected and started working normally - yet the user is still reporting delays.\n\nLooking at the timeline, the `unknown agent id \"main\"` error only appears once more at 20:11:16 (before restart), and I don't see it in logs after the restart at 20:16:44. So the error was actually resolved by my changes. The user must be experiencing something else now - maybe the delay is in how the UI itself displays sent messages, or there's a separate issue with message rendering. The user's description of \"点击发送之后，要等时间才会看到我的信息发出去了\" suggests the UI is slow to display their sent message, not that the gateway is slow to process it. The issue might be that messages are reaching the gateway fine, but the Control UI isn't updating properly after the reconnection. I should check if there's a session binding issue or if the Control UI needs a full page reload to properly sync after reconnecting. The Control UI is likely auto-reconnecting and restoring the previous session, but the slow message display could stem from WebSocket latency, UI rendering delays, or session state issues. Let me focus on the most probable causes and suggest practical fixes rather than getting bogged down in debugging the session management details. The issue is likely that the session is bound to `agent:main:main` (main agent), and after restarting the gateway and adding the main agent back, there's a session mismatch causing the UI to hang while waiting for a response. Looking at the sessions data, most are from `agent:fast_agent:...` with only one `agent:main:main` session from an hour ago, which suggests the session is stale but still being referenced by the Control UI.\n\nActually, I'm realizing the user has been successfully exchanging messages with me throughout this conversation, so the real problem is different—they're seeing delays in their OWN sent messages appearing in the UI, not in my responses. Since I'm receiving their messages, they are reaching the gateway and my model, but the UI isn't reflecting their sent messages properly. The issue isn't message delivery but rather the session state and UI rendering. I should suggest they force-refresh the page to reset the WebSocket connection, or check the browser console for errors if that doesn't resolve it.","thinkingSignature":"f9a621c3516c9d0dc40032ca8a9f48216033c2ffcf7506a00bb9c14837f4a41d"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n我之前一直在盯 gateway 日志，但忽略了最关键的地方——你发的消息其实一直能到达我，问题是 Control UI 端显示慢。\n\n这说明消息到达 gateway 没问题，是 **Control UI 的 WebSocket 连接或 session 状态**有问题。\n\n让我强制重置这个连接：\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_b8b5bd0660fa444b80886648","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /tmp/openclaw/openclaw-2026-04-16.log | grep -E \"(20:1[6-9]|20:2)\" | grep -E \"(agent_command|⇄ req|chat.send|send.*req)\" | tail -10 | python3 -c \"\nimport sys, json\nfor line in sys.stdin:\n    try:\n        d = json.loads(line)\n        t = d.get('time','')[:19]\n        msg = str(d.get('1', d.get('0','')))[:150]\n        print(t, msg)\n    except:\n        print(line.strip()[:150])\n\" 2>&1"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":926,"output":1016,"cacheRead":114048,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":115990,"cost":{"input":0.0002778,"output":0.0012192,"cacheRead":0.006842879999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00833988}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776342200416,"responseId":"063007b80b0000618dfdc08f4a8710d7"}}
