{"type":"message","id":"4ca20632","parentId":"569bd9e7","timestamp":"2026-04-16T12:24:42.797Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I can see the full picture clearly.\n\nThe log shows repeated `handshake timeout` at regular intervals (every ~10 seconds) from the same connection `conn=4580a98e`. This is the Control UI WebSocket connection.\n\nThe key findings:\n1. `⇄ res ✓ node.list 2185ms conn=4580a98e…750e` - The Control UI IS connected\n2. `memory-core: managed dreaming cron could not be reconciled (cron service unavailable)` - Cron service is unavailable! This is a new error after the restart.\n3. `embedded acpx runtime backend probe failed` - ACPX is failing\n\n\n4. The `node.list` call is taking 621ms to 2185ms, which is slower than expected, but that's not the bottleneck. The real issue is that there's a cron service failure preventing memory maintenance tasks from running—these tasks are scheduled to execute daily at 03:00 and 04:00, but the system can't reconcile them after the restart.\n\n5. The core problem appears to be that messages aren't actually reaching the gateway. The user is sending messages through the Control UI, but the gateway logs show no incoming messages at all—just the Control UI's own polling requests like sessions.list and chat.history. This suggests the messages are getting stuck somewhere between the UI and the gateway, or the gateway itself isn't processing them from the queue.\n\n6. I'm wondering if there's a mismatch between what the Control UI thinks is happening and what's actually reaching the gateway. The `unknown agent id \"main\"` error I added a fix for was from before the restart, but if it's still occurring in the current session, that could explain why messages aren't being processed—the gateway might be rejecting them at the queue level before it even tries to route them.\n\n7. The cron service failure could be compounding this. If scheduled maintenance jobs aren't running, the session store might be in a stale state that prevents new messages from being accepted or processed properly. So the gateway itself is running fine, but something in the cron-dependent services is broken. The real issue is that there's no actual user message reaching the gateway at all—nothing in the logs shows a request hitting the server. This points to a client-side problem where the Control UI either isn't sending the message or the message is getting lost before it reaches the server. The \"发出去\" delay the user is seeing could actually be a UI feedback issue rather than a network or gateway problem. Let me reconsider whether messages are even leaving the client in the first place.\n\nI should check if there's a version mismatch between the Control UI and gateway—they might be on different protocols now in v2026.4.14. Or maybe the problem is downstream; if the agent is stuck processing something slow like a large context or a thinking model, the UI could be blocking waiting for confirmation that the message was sent, even though the network request went through fine. Let me trace through what happens after a message is sent to see where it's getting stuck.\n\nThe gateway is responding quickly to sessions.list requests, so it's not the bottleneck. The messages aren't even reaching the gateway in the first place. This points to the Control UI client itself having an issue—maybe it's on an old version or there's something wrong with how it's sending messages. I should check if there's a newer version of the Control UI available that might fix this, and look for any error messages or logs on the client side.","thinkingSignature":"55c6528d5ef692f8bbb4e754750f94ba5fee6c796e7149db88108317bef57ad1"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n发现一个关键错误：`memory-core: managed dreaming cron could not be reconciled (cron service unavailable)`。Cron 服务不可用，但这个不是导致消息慢的原因。\n\n真正的问题是：**你的消息根本没有到达 gateway**。日志里没有任何 `⇄ req` 入口记录，只有 Control UI 的轮询。\n\n可能的原因：\n1. Control UI 版本和 gateway 不匹配\n2. WebSocket 握手成功但消息发送被客户端阻塞\n\n让我检查 Control UI 的版本：\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_19f3b0dc9585414a95781c0f","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s http://127.0.0.1:3102/ 2>&1 | head -5; echo \"---\"; curl -s http://127.0.0.1:3102/__openclaw__/canvas/ 2>&1 | head -5"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_ca2ed87fe2da4e5c99718cf1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /tmp/openclaw/openclaw-2026-04-16.log | grep -E \"(webchat connected|webchat.*v2026)\" | tail -5 | python3 -c \"\nimport sys, json\nfor line in sys.stdin:\n    try:\n        d = json.loads(line)\n        print(d.get('time','')[:19], str(d.get('1',''))[:120])\n    except:\n        print(line.strip()[:120])\n\" 2>&1"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":4106,"output":996,"cacheRead":116800,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":121902,"cost":{"input":0.0012318,"output":0.0011952,"cacheRead":0.0070079999999999995,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.009434999999999999}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776342262488,"responseId":"063007f6ee04d0e6d55179a3f1206355"}}
