{"type":"message","id":"c9142603","parentId":"a444fa8d","timestamp":"2026-04-16T12:25:03.166Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Control UI is connecting at `conn=4580a98e` with version v2026.4.14, matching the gateway version. The connection is fine.\n\nBut there's still no message traffic. This is really puzzling. The messages from the user ARE coming through to me (I can see them in this conversation), but gateway logs don't show them.\n\nWait - I need to think about this differently. The user is talking to ME (the AI agent on the main session). The messages are routing through the main session somehow. But gateway logs don't show `⇄ req.*agent` for the main agent...\n\nActually, maybe the messages ARE reaching the main session, but through a different mechanism than the typical agent command path. \n\nSo the issue might be that the gateway isn't logging these messages at all, or they're being routed through a path that doesn't get logged. Let me check the gateway logs more carefully - specifically looking for when a webchat message actually triggers the main agent versus just showing up in the sessions list.\n\nThe real problem is starting to make sense: when I added the `main` agent back with a new workspace path, the session IDs changed, so the old session history isn't being found. And if the Control UI is waiting for a response from the old session that doesn't exist anymore, that would explain why messages appear to send but then nothing happens.\n\nBut the gateway logs don't show any incoming `⇄ req.*chat.send` calls after restart, which is odd—the user's messages ARE reaching me somehow, so they must be getting through something.\n\nActually, I think I've got it: the Control UI connects via WebSocket to the gateway, sends messages through that WebSocket connection, and the responses come back the same way. If there's a mismatch between what the UI is trying to do and what the gateway expects, that would explain the delay without necessarily showing up in the logs as a clear error. Let me check the WebSocket connection state more carefully.\n\nWait, I need to correct myself—the user is sending messages through the Control UI at `localhost:3102`, which routes to the gateway, which then forwards them to the agent. So the messages are actually coming through the main session, not bypassing it entirely.\n\nLet me check if the Control UI is properly sending messages through the WebSocket connection rather than some other path. I should look at the raw WebSocket frames or check the gateway's RPC logs to see what's actually being transmitted. But actually, I'm now realizing something important: the user is talking to me in this very conversation, so my responses ARE going through somehow. The question is whether they're going through the main agent's normal reply mechanism or if something else is at play.\n\nLet me step back and think about what could cause the \"发出信息要等时间\" issue. It could be a slow model response, something blocking before the model even gets called, or a slow network round-trip between the gateway and the channel. I've ruled out `unknown agent id \"main\"` since the hot reload fixed that. Now I need to consider if there's something about how the webchat channel is routing messages that's causing the delay.\n\nThe user mentioned that before upgrading to v2026.4.14, there was no such issue, so the upgrade itself introduced this problem. The changelog mentions something about Telegram/forum topics, but that doesn't seem relevant here. More importantly, I notice the `unknown agent id \"main\"` error existed before the restart—that's likely what was causing the slowdown. After the restart, the main agent is now properly registered, so the question is whether the user is still experiencing delays now that the agent configuration has been fixed. The gateway is processing requests normally based on the logs—sessions.list and chat.history are responding quickly, and there are no error messages. I should ask the user to send a test message so I can observe the gateway logs in real-time and see what's actually happening.","thinkingSignature":"b1b53fba58fa2b17315ef8e4b5f199236f6e72018d651b64087e2da1eabed098"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nControl UI 版本匹配（v2026.4.14），连接正常。\n\n日志里没有消息入口记录这个问题很关键。我直接问你：\n\n你现在发一条消息，看回复快不快？如果还是慢，请告诉我大概等了多少秒——1秒？5秒？10秒？我需要这个数字来判断慢是在哪个阶段。"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":682,"output":861,"cacheRead":120896,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":122439,"cost":{"input":0.00020459999999999999,"output":0.0010332,"cacheRead":0.00725376,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.008491559999999999}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776342283539,"responseId":"0630080acd8138291b1ca19dc8203773"}}
