{"type":"message","id":"ebec9492","parentId":"3ebeb15c","timestamp":"2026-04-16T12:26:41.457Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Still no message from the user in the gateway log. The user's message is not reaching the gateway. This is the core issue.\n\nThe user's messages are NOT reaching the gateway at all. This is a WebSocket connectivity issue on the client side.\n\nLet me think about what could cause this:\n1. The Control UI WebSocket connects but then fails to send messages\n2. The messages are queued somewhere but never reach the gateway\n3. There's a client-side issue\n\nActually, wait. The user sent \"我发\" and I see chat.history/sessions.list responses - these are responses to the Control UI's own polling. The user's message IS reaching the gateway... wait, no. If the message had reached the gateway, there would be a corresponding request log entry for it.\n \nI'm realizing the distinction between the Control UI's polling requests and actual user messages - the fact that the gateway logged the Control UI's polling responses means it processed those requests, but that doesn't mean the user's message actually arrived. Let me check if there was a new message sent by looking at the timestamps more carefully.\n\nThe gateway is receiving polling requests fine, but the user's actual message might be getting stuck on the client side before it even reaches the gateway. The Control UI could be failing to transmit the message through its WebSocket connection even though the connection itself is active and responding to pings.\n\nBut if my own messages are reaching the gateway through this same session, then the WebSocket path is clearly working. That suggests the issue is specifically with how the user's message is being handled on the Control UI side - maybe the input field isn't properly triggering the send, or there's something blocking the message from entering the queue.\n\nLet me think about this differently. The user is reporting that after clicking send, they have to wait before their message actually gets sent. That's a client-side delay - the UI is taking time to process or queue the message before transmitting it through the WebSocket.\n\nThe \"等待时间\" they mentioned is likely the time between clicking send and seeing the message leave their client. This could mean the Control UI is slow to encode the message, the model is taking time to generate a response, or the UI is waiting for gateway confirmation before displaying the sent message.\n\nSince I can't see the actual timing, I should ask them to measure it. But actually, the most actionable issue I can address is that I haven't been getting logs of their messages at all - that suggests the Control UI isn't successfully sending the message data through the WebSocket connection, which would definitely cause a noticeable delay.\n\nThe real question is whether clicking \"send\" in the Control UI triggers any WebSocket traffic at all, or if something is blocking the message from being transmitted in the first place. Without being able to see the client's WebSocket outgoing queue, I should focus on what I can actually verify and fix.\n\nActually, I'm noticing the gateway log shows only Control UI's own traffic (sessions.list, chat.history, node.list polling) but nothing from the user, even though the user is clearly sending messages through this same connection. That discrepancy is odd. But the user confirmed messages are being sent from their end, so they must be transmitted eventually. The issue might be that they're measuring the wrong thing - they're watching for their message to appear on screen, but the delay could be from waiting for the AI response, not from the message transmission itself.\n\nSince the user's messages ARE getting through to me (I receive them), I should ask them to test by sending a simple message and timing how long it takes to appear on screen, and separately how long until they get an AI reply. That'll tell us where the bottleneck actually is. Actually, let me check the session data directly to see what's stored there.","thinkingSignature":"6579035a9bda49b34cd7b96d5224d65721c171059d50bd34e34b62f779de4556"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n日志里依然没有用户消息的入口。但我知道你在发——你的消息我能收到。\n\n问题锁定在：**你的消息能到我（我收到了），但 gateway 日志里没有记录**。这说明消息走的是另一条路径，不是通过 `agent_command` 的标准入口。\n\n让我直接看 session transcript 确认消息有没有被处理：\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_6ec3b9d443644270afbe4fe1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls -lt ~/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/ | head -3"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":428,"output":864,"cacheRead":121984,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":123276,"cost":{"input":0.0001284,"output":0.0010368,"cacheRead":0.00731904,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00848424}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776342384002,"responseId":"0630086ff503e3ca9d96ccff00a0d2b2"}}
