{"type":"message","id":"19c307fd","parentId":"eae04a3d","timestamp":"2026-04-16T12:29:31.590Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK so the user is saying the issue is that when they click send, the message takes time to appear on screen. This is a frontend issue - the message is being sent from the UI to the gateway, and the UI should show it immediately when it's sent.\n\nThis could be:\n1. The Control UI is waiting for gateway acknowledgment before showing the message\n2. The WebSocket connection is slow to send\n3. The Control UI has some blocking operation before showing the message\n\nThis is a client-side issue. Let me look at the Control UI side. Actually, I can't directly see the Control UI logs since it's a browser-based app.\n\nBut wait - let me think about what happens when you click send in Control UI:\n\n\n1. You type message and click send\n2. Control UI sends the message over WebSocket to gateway\n3. Gateway receives and processes it\n4. Gateway sends back an acknowledgment/response\n5. Control UI shows the message\n\nIf step 2 or 3 is slow, the message wouldn't appear immediately. The fact that the user says it \"takes time\" suggests there's a delay in this flow. Actually, thinking about it more carefully - if the WebSocket is sending the message and waiting for a response before showing it, that would explain the delay. The gateway would need to receive and process the message first.\n\nBut actually, most UIs show the message immediately and then update when they get a response back. The fact that it's slow suggests the gateway might be processing the message before acknowledging it, or there's something blocking the send. Let me look at the chat.send request timing - the logs showed `⇄ res ✓ chat.send 89ms` which means it takes 89ms for the gateway to respond to a send. That's not slow at all. So the gateway is fast, but the UI isn't showing the message immediately.\n\nThis is puzzling - the gateway responds in 89ms but the user still experiences delay. Let me think about what could be causing this. Maybe there's an issue with the WebSocket connection or the UI's message handling logic. Or perhaps the gateway isn't responding properly to chat.send requests.","thinkingSignature":"f4a68a057f5b31231d2aac9e8141c6bef383beab9954a353cf19864549ef15df"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n明白了，这是 Control UI 端的问题——点发送后界面要等才显示。\n\n让我看一下 `chat.send` 在 gateway 端的处理路径：\n\n```\nchat.send → gateway → 立即返回 → UI显示\n```\n\ngateway 的 `chat.send` 只要 89ms，理论上很快。问题可能在 Control UI 这边——它可能在等 gateway 返回 `runId` 才开始显示消息。\n\n看 Control UI 发消息后的日志：\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_9ec06b67e8a641c4aab7ae4c","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /tmp/openclaw/openclaw-2026-04-16.log | grep \"⇄ req.*chat.send\" | tail -5 | python3 -c \"\nimport sys, json\nfor line in sys.stdin:\n    try:\n        d = json.loads(line)\n        t = d.get('time','')[:19]\n        msg = str(d.get('1',''))\n        print(t, msg[:150])\n    except:\n        print(line.strip()[:150])\n\" 2>&1"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":122,"output":651,"cacheRead":125376,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":126149,"cost":{"input":0.000036599999999999995,"output":0.0007812,"cacheRead":0.007522559999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00834036}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776342557262,"responseId":"0630091b0107e00d84545fba3fc6eca3"}}
