{"type":"message","id":"ce303f40","parentId":"7a71a6e5","timestamp":"2026-04-16T12:35:03.775Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user says if I turn off thinking, they can't get back in. So the `thinking: \"off\"` in agents.defaults makes the gateway unable to start or something? Or maybe it's a different kind of \"can't get in\".\n\nActually, maybe the issue is that when I set `thinking: \"off\"` as default, it applies to ALL sessions including the current one. But the user is saying they can't get in - meaning the gateway might have crashed or the Control UI can't connect.\n\nActually wait - I did restart the gateway with `thinking: \"off\"` in defaults. But if the gateway couldn't start or something went wrong... but the systemctl restart got SIGTERM which means the process was killed, not that it failed.\n \nLet me check what the actual error was. The user might be saying that with thinking disabled, they can't connect to the gateway - which could mean the setting is blocking their access somehow, or maybe the gateway crashed and they can't get back in because of that.\n\nActually, thinking about it more carefully - if the gateway is running but the Control UI shows the thinking setting as \"off\", maybe the user is worried that if they refresh or lose connection, they won't be able to get back in because something about the configuration prevents it. Or perhaps they're saying that disabling thinking makes the system unusable in some way they can't recover from.\n\nThe real issue is probably that I changed `agents.defaults.thinking` to \"off\" and restarted, which affected the current session. If they're using the current session (main agent with think:adaptive), disabling thinking might have locked them out somehow, or they're worried about losing access if the session changes.\n\nI should probably just revert the thinking setting back to what it was before - which was actually unset (not \"adaptive\"), so the gateway would use its default behavior. That seems safer than leaving it off entirely.","thinkingSignature":"f6e89e4743274ff357ba3853c7ce0f199041da0f18bd709997f53b63f39ee784"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n好，马上恢复：\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_fce50ed78a3e43c08ed60537","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 << 'EOF'\nimport json\n\npath = '/home/ai/.openclaw/openclaw.json'\nwith open(path) as f:\n    d = json.load(sys.stdin) if False else json.load(f)\n\n# Remove the thinking setting I added\nif 'thinking' in d['agents']['defaults']:\n    del d['agents']['defaults']['thinking']\n\nwith open(path, 'w') as f:\n    json.dump(d, f, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False)\n\nprint(\"Reverted. thinking removed from defaults\")\nEOF"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":165,"output":517,"cacheRead":126144,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":126826,"cost":{"input":0.0000495,"output":0.0006204,"cacheRead":0.00756864,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.008238539999999999}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776342887684,"responseId":"06300a68c7b96b35401215567ff8de52"}}
