{"type":"message","id":"1d47433b","parentId":"1cfc02a1","timestamp":"2026-04-16T12:37:07.314Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK, so after restart, a new session still has the same slow speed. This rules out the old session being the problem. The issue is system-wide.\n\nLet me think about what changed between v2026.4.9 and v2026.4.14 that could cause this.\n\nFrom the changelog:\n1. OpenAI Codex/models: forward-compat support for gpt-5.4.4-pro\n2. Telegram/forum topics: surface human topic names\n3. Agents/Ollama: forward the configured embedded-run timeout into the global undici s...\n4. Assistant: ...forward `model` param to LLM APIs\n\n5. Models/Codex: bundled Codex provider - `codex/gpt-*` models use Codex-managed auth, native threads, model discovery, and compaction\n\nWait - \"forward the configured embedded-run timeout into the global undici s\" - this might be related to HTTP client configuration. Maybe the timeout behavior changed?\n \nActually, I'm noticing something about the thinking mode. The runtime shows `think:adaptive` and I configured `thinking: \"off\"` in defaults, but the session is still running in adaptive mode. That suggests the setting might be getting overridden at the session level, or perhaps the new session is inheriting the thinking mode from somewhere else in the config rather than respecting the default I set.\n\nLooking at the changelog entries more carefully, I see references to both \"forward-compat support for gpt-5.4.4-pro\" and \"bundled Codex provider\" which might be affecting how thinking is handled across different model types. I'm going in circles trying to diagnose this when the issue is clear: after the update to v2026.4.14, something about how MiniMax-M2.7 processes requests or how the thinking mode behaves has changed. The changelog mentions \"forward `model` param to LLM APIs\" which could have altered the request format or parameters being sent. Since the user is running `think:adaptive`, maybe that's where the slowdown originates, but I can't disable it without breaking their session. Let me check if there's a way to set thinking to \"off\" on a per-session basis instead of globally.\n\nActually, I should step back and look at the actual request flow. The session shows MiniMax-M2.7 at 122k/205k tokens with 59% usage, which is quite high. If there's an active memory plugin running before each reply, that's adding overhead even without my recent changes. And I need to check what `chat.send` in the gateway is actually doing—it might be blocking on something.\n\nLooking at the `chat.send` logs, the response time was 89ms, so that's not the bottleneck. Let me trace the actual message flow from when you click send in the UI to when it appears on screen. The Control UI might be sending via WebSocket and waiting for a `runId` before displaying the message, then receiving streaming chunks from the server. If the UI isn't showing the message immediately while waiting for `runId`, that would explain the delay you're seeing.\n\nThe real question is why the entire pipeline got slower after upgrading from v2026.4.9 to v2026.4.14. I should check what changed in how MiniMax handles requests or if there's something about the new version that affects streaming or message handling. Let me ask when exactly the slowdown started—whether it began immediately after upgrading or only after certain events like adding the main agent. And I need to look more carefully at the CHANGELOG to see what changed in v2026.4.14 that could explain this.\n\nLooking at the Ollama timeout change: \"forward the configured embedded-run timeout into the global undici socket\" —this means Ollama requests now respect the embedded-run timeout through the HTTP client, which could cause requests to fail earlier if they're not completing in time. But the session is using MiniMax-M2.7, not Ollama, so this wouldn't directly affect the main session. Unless there's a fallback happening that's causing the slowdown.\n\nI'm also wondering if the v2026.4.14 update changed how the MiniMax API handles requests—maybe the model is running slower now due to server-side changes. Or maybe there's a session management change that increased context loading overhead. Actually, let me reconsider the session count. The session list shows 20 entries total, including main, subagents, and other agents, but the user's actual agent is `agent:main:main`. The `think:adaptive` setting is coming from the Control UI or the session configuration itself, not the global defaults.\n\nSince I can't disable thinking globally, let me try a different approach—set the default model to a faster one for the main agent to see if that improves speed, or check if there's a `thinking` field in the openclaw.json that might be controlling this session-level setting. Actually, I should ask the user directly what they want me to do here.\n\nWait, I'm going in circles. The real issue is that after upgrading to v2026.4.14, something in the request/response pipeline changed. Looking at what the changelog says was fixed—\"forward `model` param to LLM APIs\"—this might have fixed a bug where the model parameter wasn't being passed correctly before, and now that it's being passed properly, the behavior is different. If the model is doing something it wasn't before, like additional processing or a different output format, that could explain the slowdown.\n\nLet me just ask the user for more specific details about when exactly the slowdown started and whether it's consistent or intermittent.","thinkingSignature":"f1272b34383e6574b5a5e02f420cb12e70662569982b0912de9454c8c5830e20"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n没差别说明不是旧 session 的问题，是全局的。\n\n升级后变慢这个现象，我的判断是：**v2026.4.14 某个变更影响了 MiniMax 请求的行为**。具体是 model 参数传递方式变正确了、还是 API 侧有变化，不确定。\n\n你现在有几个选择：\n\n1. **回滚到 v2026.4.9** — 最保守，确保没问题\n2. **继续用 v2026.4.14**，我帮你开一个新的 minimal workspace 测试，是不是只有这个 workspace 的 session 慢\n3. **确认一下**：这个现象是所有 session 都慢，还是只有你常用那个？新开一个 session（换个浏览器或无痕模式）是否还是一样慢？"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":133,"output":1293,"cacheRead":126592,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":128018,"cost":{"input":0.0000399,"output":0.0015516,"cacheRead":0.00759552,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00918702}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776343000080,"responseId":"06300ad6f17e8162a8ca3ac7b74dca75"}}
